# Cancer Mage
# Ability Name				Unique Key										Category of Ability		Type															Define																	Description																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																		Ability																			Bonus DC					Modify VAR																											Source Page		Aspects
Weapon and Armor Proficiency		KEY:Cancer Mage ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Cancer Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality																								DESC:Cancer mages are proficient with all simple and martial weapons, with all types of armor, and with shields.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																	ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|TYPE=ArmorProfHeavy|TYPE=ShieldProf|TYPE=WeaponProfMartial																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.52
Sneak Attack				KEY:Cancer Mage ~ Sneak Attack						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Cancer Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality			DEFINE:CancerMageSneakAttackLVL|0													DESC:If a cancer mage can catch an opponent when she is unable to defend herself effectively from his attack, he can strike a vital spot for extra damage. Basically, any time the cancer mage's target would be denied her Dexterity bonus to AC (whether she actually has a Dexterity bonus or not), the cancer mage's attack deals +1d6 points of damage. This extra damage increases by +1d6 points every four levels (+2d6 at 5th level and +3d6 at 9th level). Should the cancer mage score a critical hit with a sneak attack, this extra damage is not multiplied. It takes precision and penetration to hit a vital spot, so ranged attacks can only count as sneak attacks if the target is 30 feet away or less. With a sap or an unarmed strike, a cancer mage can make a sneak attack that deals subdual damage instead of normal damage. He cannot use a weapon that deals normal damage to deal subdual damage in a sneak attack, not even with the usual -4 penalty, because he must make optimal use of his weapon in order to execute the sneak attack. A cancer mage can only sneak attack a living creature with a discernible anatomy-undead, constructs, oozes, plants, and incorporeal creatures lack vital areas to attack. Additionally, any creature immune to critical hits is similarly immune to sneak attacks. Also, the cancer mage must be able to see the target well enough to pick out a vital spot and must be able to reach a vital spot. A cancer mage cannot sneak attack while striking at a creature with concealment or by striking the limbs of a creature whose vitals are beyond reach. If a cancer mage gets a sneak attack bonus from another source (such as rogue levels), the bonuses to damage stack.																																																																																																																																																																				BONUS:VAR|SneakAttackDice|(CancerMageSneakAttackLVL+3)/4																			SOURCEPAGE:p.52	BONUS:VAR|CancerMageSneakAttackLVL|CancerMageLVL
Disease Host				KEY:Cancer Mage ~ Disease Host						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Cancer Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:At 1st level, a cancer mage suffers no ill effects of diseases, except for purely cosmetic ones such as boils, pockmarks, watery eyes, blackened skin, hair loss, foul smell, and so on. The cancer mage becomes a carrier of every disease he encounters, though he remains immune to most of their effects. However, the cancer mage takes 1d6 points of damage per caster level if someone casts a cure disease spell or effect on him (he can make a Fortitude save to try to resist the effect). Furthermore, if the cancer mage has a cancerous companion (see below), he loses all abilities gained from the companion for 1d10 days after being the subject of a cure disease spell.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.53
Contagion					KEY:Cancer Mage ~ Contagion							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Cancer Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						DESC:Beginning at 2nd level, the touch of a cancer mage carries a contagion spell once per day per class level. The DC for the target's saving throw is 13 + the cancer mage's Wisdom modifier.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.53	BONUS:VAR|ContagionPerDay|CancerMageLVL	BONUS:VAR|ContagionLVL|CancerMageLVL
Cancerous Companion			KEY:Cancer Mage ~ Cancerous Companion					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Cancer Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:At 2nd level, a cancer grows within the cancer mage, forming a large tumor. This cancerous growth gains intelligence and a personality distinct from the cancer mage. The companion and the cancer mage can communicate telepathically. When needed, the cancerous companion uses the cancer mage's scores for saves, ability scores other than Intelligence, and so forth. The cancerous companion gains abilities as the cancer mage gains levels.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.53	BONUS:VAR|CancerousCompanionLVL|CancerMageLVL
Tatterdemalion				KEY:Cancer Mage ~ Tatterdemalion						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Cancer Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:Gathering scraps of clothing and old, discarded rags, a 3rd-level cancer mage is able to make such articles into light armor with a the following stats: armor bonus +4, maximum Dex bonus +5, armor check penalty -1, arcane spell failure 15%%, speed 30 ft./20 ft., weight 20 lb. Only a 3rd-level or higher cancer mage can wear this armor and gain these benefits; other wearers treat it as padded armor. This armor is considered masterwork quality and can be fashioned into magic armor.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.53
Poison					KEY:Cancer Mage ~ Poison							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Cancer Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						DESC:Once per day per class level beginning at 3rd level, the touch of a cancer mage carries a poison spell. The DC for the target's saving throw is 14 + the cancer mage's Wisdom modifier.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.53	BONUS:VAR|PoisonPerDay|CancerMageLVL	BONUS:VAR|PoisonLVL|CancerMageLVL
Children of the Night			KEY:Cancer Mage ~ Children of the Night					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Cancer Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:A 4th-level cancer mage commands the lesser creatures of the world and can call forth a swarm of 2d6 Small monstrous spiders or a pack of 4d8 dire rats or a swarm of 10d10 bats, once per day, as a standard action. These creatures arrive in 2d6 rounds and serve the cancer mage (understanding his mental commands) for up to 10 minutes per class level.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.53
Viral Agent					KEY:Cancer Mage ~ Viral Agent							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Cancer Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:At 5th level, a cancer mage befriends a disease or virus that infests his body. He supernaturally enhances a disease, making it smarter by giving it a point of his own Intelligence. He establishes a telepathic link with the disease that functions at a range of one mile per class level of the cancer mage. The cancer mage can then attempt to infect a target with his viral agent, using his contagion ability. If successful, the viral agent can tell the cancer mage telepathically what its host experiences. In all other respects, the viral agent is a normal disease; if the victim fights it off or a cure disease spell is used, the disease and the viral agent die. The cancer mage regains his Intelligence point 24 hours after the viral agent dies. The cancer mage can create as many viral agents as he is willing to devote Intelligence points toward.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																											SOURCEPAGE:p.53
Infected Wound				KEY:Cancer Mage ~ Infected Wound						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Cancer Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality			DEFINE:CancerMageInfectedWoundLVL|0													DESC:Once per day per class level beginning at 6th level, a cancer mage can infect his foe with an infectious taint after making a successful melee attack. The foe takes 1 point of Constitution damage and must make a Fortitude save (DC 10 + cancer mage's class level + cancer mage's Wis modifier) 1 hour later or take a further 1d6 points of Constitution damage.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																	BONUS:VAR|InfectedWoundPerDay|CancerMageInfectedWoundLVL	BONUS:VAR|InfectedWoundDC|CancerMageInfectedWoundLVL										SOURCEPAGE:p.53	BONUS:VAR|CancerMageInfectedWoundLVL|CancerMageLVL
Insect Plague				KEY:Cancer Mage ~ Insect Plague						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Cancer Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						DESC:At 7th level, a cancer mage invokes insect plague once per day as a cleric of his class level.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.53	BONUS:VAR|InsectPlaguePerDay|1	BONUS:VAR|InsectPlagueLVL|CancerMageLVL
Insect Armor				KEY:Cancer Mage ~ Insect Armor						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Cancer Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:By allowing insects and worms to crawl over his body, a 7th-level cancer mage gains a +4 natural armor bonus. The cancer mage cannot wear armor heavier than light armor and keep this benefit, however.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.53
Viral Ally					KEY:Cancer Mage ~ Viral Ally							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Cancer Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:In a fashion similar to the viral agent ability, a cancer mage of 8th level or higher can create a viral ally by devoting 3 points of Intelligence to a disease or virus in his system. The cancer mage can then bestow his viral ally upon a humanoid victim using his contagion ability, and the viral ally can communicate telepathically with the cancer mage. The viral ally (and thus the cancer mage) controls its host as surely as with a dominate person spell, although the host gets no separate saving throw to avoid the dominate person effect. The viral ally is a normal disease, however, and the victim can fight it off with successful Fortitude saves or a cure disease spell, either of which kills the viral ally. The cancer mage regains his missing Intelligence points 24 hours later. A cancer mage can create as many viral allies as he is willing to devote Intelligence points toward.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.54
Disease Form				KEY:Cancer Mage ~ Disease Form						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Cancer Mage Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:At 10th level, a cancer mage gains the ability to tranform into a disease once per day. (This ability also affects up to 100 pounds of gear the cancer mage is carrying, plus tatterdemalion armor, insect armor, and a cancerous companion.) As a disease, the cancer mage is intangible and invisible to standard methods of observation, even blindsight. Creatures with the scent ability note a foulness in the air. The cancer mage cannot move, except with the wind (if any), or within a host. The cancer mage may adopt his disease form as a standard action, attempting to infect a living creature within 100 feet. A potential victim must succeed at a Fortitude save (DC 20) to avoid being infected with the cancer mage. Any creature that comes within 10 feet of a cancer mage in disease form is subject to the saving throw to resist infection as well. Once inside an infected host, the cancer mage deals 1d3 points of Constitution damage per day after a 24-hour incubation period. The victim has no way of knowing that the cancer mage is anything other than a normal illness. The cancer mage travels with the victim, aware of whatever the victim is aware of. A number of times per day equal to the cancer mage's Charisma bonus, the cancer mage can attempt to force the victim to take one round's worth of actions of the cancer mage's choosing; a successful Will save (DC 18 + cancer mage's Wis modifier) allows the victim to resist this. While controlling his victim, the cancer mage has access to all skills, feats, spells, and special abilities of the host, plus any of his own that he can use in his disembodied state. The cancer mage can leave his host at any time, allowing the victim to recover normally. The victim can also attempt to force the cancer mage out by making Fortitude saves as if the cancer mage were a normal disease. Heal checks help the victim as they would normally. A cure disease spell kills the cancer mage if he fails a Fortitude save (calculating the save DC as for spells of the same level). Even if the cancer mage succeeds at the saving throw, he is forced to reassume his material form adjacent to the victim. A cancer mage can remain in disease form as long as he desires, or he can return to his natural form and be done with the disease form for that day. While in disease form, the cancer mage does not need to eat, sleep, or drink, and he does not age. A cancer mage could remain dormant in a room for a hundred years, then take his material form or infect a new victim.																											BONUS:VAR|DiseaseFormTimes|1																								SOURCEPAGE:p.54

# Demonologist
Weapon and Armor Proficiency		KEY:Demonologist ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Demonologist Class Feature.SpecialQuality																							DESC:Demonologists are proficient with no weapons, armor, or shields.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.55
Spells					KEY:Demonologist ~ Spells							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Demonologist Class Feature.SpecialQuality																							DESC:Beginning at 1st level, a demonologist gains the ability to cast a small number of arcane spells. To cast a spell, the demonologist must have a Charisma score of at least 10 + the spell's level, so a demonologist with a Charisma of 10 or lower cannot cast these spells. Demonologist bonus spells are based on Charisma, and saving throws against these spells have a DC of 10 + spell level + Charisma modifier. The demonologist's spell list appears below; a demonologist has access to any spell on the list and need not prepare those spells ahead of time, just like a sorcerer. A demonologist casts spells just as a sorcerer does.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.55
Charm Demon					KEY:Demonologist ~ Charm Demon						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Demonologist Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						DESC:A 1st-level demonologist can attempt to charm a chaotic evil outsider, as described in the charm person spell, once per day. The demon does not get to use its spell resistance, though it can make a saving throw as normal (DC 11 + demonologist's Cha modifier).																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.55	BONUS:VAR|CharmDemonPerDay|1	BONUS:VAR|CharmDemonLVL|DemonologistLVL
Quasit Familiar				KEY:Demonologist ~ Quasit Familiar						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Demonologist Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:A 2nd-level demonologist gains a quasit as a familiar, whether he wants it or not. If the demonologist already has a familiar, the quasit devours it and takes its place, but the character suffers no experience point loss. The quasit is treated as a normal familiar, using the class level of the demonologist as the master's level (see the Familiars section in Chapter 3 of the Player's Handbook for familiar abilities).																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.55	BONUS:VAR|QuasitFamiliarLVL|DemonologistLVL
Summoning Mastery				KEY:Demonologist ~ Summoning Mastery					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Demonologist Class Feature.SpecialQuality			DEFINE:DemonologistSummoningMasteryLVL|0												DESC:When a demonologist of 3rd level or higher casts a summon monster spell, it is treated as the equivalent spell of two levels higher for purposes of summoning chaotic evil creatures. For example, a demonologist refers to the summon monster IV list for chaotic evil outsiders when casting summon monster II. At 6th level, the demonologist refers to the summoning list three levels higher than the one for the summon monster spell he is casting. At 9th level, the demonologist refers to the list four levels higher.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																							BONUS:VAR|SummoningMasteryListAdvancement|1+(DemonologistSummoningMasteryLVL/3)															SOURCEPAGE:p.55	BONUS:VAR|DemonologistSummoningMasteryLVL|DemonologistLVL
Resistances					KEY:Demonologist ~ Resistances						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Demonologist Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:A demonologist who reaches 4th level gains acid resistance 10, cold resistance 10, fire resistance 10, and electricity resistance 20.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																												ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Resistance To Acid|Resistance to Cold|Resistance To Electricity|Resistance To Fire							BONUS:VAR|AcidResistanceBonus|10	BONUS:VAR|ColdResistanceBonus|10	BONUS:VAR|FireResistanceBonus|10	BONUS:VAR|ElectricityResistanceBonus|20				SOURCEPAGE:p.55
Poison Immunity				KEY:Demonologist ~ Poison Immunity						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Demonologist Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:A 5thlevel demonologist is immune to poison.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.55
Hold Demon					KEY:Demonologist ~ Hold Demon							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Demonologist Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						DESC:A 7th-level demonologist can attempt to hold a chaotic evil outsider, as described in the hold person spell, once per day. The demon does not get to use its spell resistance, though it can make a saving throw as normal (DC 12 + demonologist's Cha modifier).																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.55	BONUS:VAR|HoldDemonPerDay|1	BONUS:VAR|HoldDemonLVL|DemonologistLVL
Telepathy					KEY:Demonologist ~ Telepathy							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Demonologist Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:An 8th-level demonologist can communicate telepathically with any creature within 100 feet that has a language, just as a tanar'ri can.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.55	BONUS:VAR|TelepathyRange|100
Dominate Demon				KEY:Demonologist ~ Dominate Demon						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Demonologist Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						DESC:A 10th-level demonologist can attempt to dominate a chaotic evil outsider, as described in the dominate person spell, once per day. The demon does not get its spell resistance, but it can make a saving throw as normal (DC 15 + demonologist's Cha modifier).																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.55	BONUS:VAR|DominateDemonPerDay|1	BONUS:VAR|DominateDemonLVL|DemonologistLVL

# Diabolist
Weapon and Armor Proficiency		KEY:Diabolist ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Diabolist Class Feature.SpecialQuality																								DESC:Diabolists are proficient with no weapons, armor, or shields.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.56
Spells					KEY:Diabolist ~ Spells								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Diabolist Class Feature.SpecialQuality																								DESC:When a diabolist attains 1st level, and at every level after that, the character gains new spells per day as if she had also gained a level in whatever spellcasting class she belonged to before she added the prestige class. She does not, however, gain any other benefit a character of that class would have gained (improved chance of controlling or rebuking undead, metamagic or item creation feats, hit points beyond those received from the prestige class, and so on), except for an increased effective level of spellcasting. This essentially means that she adds the new level of diabolist to the level of whatever other spellcasting class the character has, then determines spells per day, spells known, and caster level accordingly. For example, if LadyMandrake, a 9th-level sorcerer, gains a level in diabolist, she gains new spells as if she had risen to 10th level in sorcerer, but uses the other diabolist aspects of level progression such as base attack bonus and save bonuses. If she next gains a level of sorcerer, making her a 10th-level sorcerer/1st-level diabolist, she gains spells as if she had risen to 11th level as a sorcerer. If a character had more than one spellcasting class before she became a diabolist, she must decide to which class she adds the level of diabolist.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.56
Diabolism					KEY:Diabolist ~ Diabolism							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Diabolist Class Feature.SpecialQuality				DEFINE:DiabolistDiabolismLVL|0	DEFINE:DiabolismDie|0									DESC:A diabolist can choose to grant one of her spells greater magical power once per day plus one additional time for every three class levels. Any spell the diabolist casts that affects a target or area (one that does not include herself ) gains the evil descriptor and deals +1d6 points of unholy damage to any good character affected by the spell. For example, a fireball cast by a 6th-level wizard/1st-level diabolist deals 7d6 points of fire damage and 1d6 points of unholy damage. A hold person spell cast by the same diabolist holds a humanoid target motionless and deals 1d6 points of unholy damage if the target is good. At 5th level, the unholy damage increases to +2d6 points. At 10th level, the unholy damage increases to +3d6 points.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																	BONUS:VAR|DiabolismDie|6	BONUS:VAR|Diabolism|DiabolistDiabolismLVL/5	BONUS:VAR|DiabolismPerDay|1+(DiabolistDiabolismLVL/3)							SOURCEPAGE:p.56	BONUS:VAR|DiabolistDiabolismLVL|DiabolistLVL
Imp Familiar				KEY:Diabolist ~ Imp Familiar							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Diabolist Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						DESC:A 2nd-level diabolist gains an imp as a familiar, whether she wants it or not. If the diabolist already has a familiar, the imp devours it and takes its place. The imp is treated as a normal familiar, using the class level of the diabolist as the wizard's level (see the Familiars section in Chapter 3 of the Player's Handbook for familiar abilities).																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.57	BONUS:VAR|ImpFamiliarLVL|DiabolistLVL
Vile Diabolism				KEY:Diabolist ~ Vile Diabolism						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Diabolist Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						DESC:An 8th-level diabolist can use her diabolism power to deal half the normal amount of extra unholy damage as vile damage (see Chapter 2 for an explanation of vile damage). For example, a fireball cast by a 6th-level wizard/8th-level diabolist deals 10d6 points of fire damage and 2d6 points of unholy damage. If the diabolist then rolls a 7 for the 2d6 points of unholy damage, she can (if she chooses) convert the unholy damage into 3 points of vile damage instead.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																											SOURCEPAGE:p.57

# Disciple of Asmodeus
Weapon and Armor Proficiency		KEY:Disciple of Asmodeus ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Disciple of Asmodeus Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						DESC:Disciples of Asmodeus are proficient with no weapons, armor, or shields.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.58
Spells					KEY:Disciple of Asmodeus ~ Spells						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Disciple of Asmodeus Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						DESC:When a disciple of Asmodeus attains 1st level, and at every other level after that, the character gains new spells per day as if he had also gained a level in whatever spellcasting class he belonged to before he added the prestige class. He does not, however, gain any other benefit a character of that class would have gained (improved chance of controlling or rebuking undead, metamagic or item creation feats, hit points beyond those received from the prestige class, and so on), except for an increased effective level of spellcasting. This essentially means that he adds the new level of disciple of Asmodeus to the level of whatever other spellcasting class the character has, then determines spells per day, spells known, and caster level accordingly. For example, if Ulthanc, an 8th-level wizard, gains a level in disciple of Asmodeus, he gains new spells as if he had risen to 9th level in wizard, but uses the other disciple of Asmodeus aspects of level progression such as base attack bonus and save bonus. If he next gains a level of wizard, making him a 9th-level wizard/1st-level disciple of Asmodeus, he gains spells as if he had risen to 10th level as a wizard. If a character had more than one spellcasting class before he became a disciple of Asmodeus, he must decide to which class he adds the level of disciple of Asmodeus.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.58
Charm						KEY:Disciple of Asmodeus ~ Charm						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Disciple of Asmodeus Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:Once per day, a disciple of Asmodeus can produce an effect identical to that of a charm person spell cast by a spellcaster of his effective caster level.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.58	BONUS:VAR|CharmPersonPerDay|1	BONUS:VAR|CharmPersonLVL|DiscipleOfAsmodeusLVL
Learn Secret				KEY:Disciple of Asmodeus ~ Learn Secret					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Disciple of Asmodeus Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:Through trickery, deceit, and sometimes even intimidation, a disciple of Asmodeus can learn secrets otherwise unattainable. At 1st level, the disciple can make a Gather Information check once per week with a +10 competency bonus. For every two levels beyond 1st level, the disciple of Asmodeus can use this ability one more time per week (twice at 3rd level, three times at 5th level, and so on) until 9th level, when the disciple of Asmodeus can use the ability once per day.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.58
Command					KEY:Disciple of Asmodeus ~ Command						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Disciple of Asmodeus Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:Once per day, a 2nd-level disciple of Asmodeus can produce an effect identical to that of a command spell cast by a spellcaster of his effective caster level.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.58	BONUS:VAR|CommandPerDay|1	BONUS:VAR|CommandLVL|DiscipleOfAsmodeusLVL
Summon Hellcat				KEY:Disciple of Asmodeus ~ Summon Hellcat					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Disciple of Asmodeus Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:A 4th-level disciple of Asmodeus can summon 1 hellcat once per day. This functions as a summon monster spell cast by a spellcaster of his effective caster level. A 9th-level disciple of Asmodeus gains the ability to summon 1d4 hellcats once per day.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.58
Evil Authority				KEY:Disciple of Asmodeus ~ Evil Authority					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Disciple of Asmodeus Class Feature.SpecialQuality		DEFINE:DiscipleOfAsmodeusEvilAuthorityLVL|0	DEFINE:EvilAuthorityPerDay|0	DEFINE:EvilAuthorityDC|0	DESC:Once per day, at the command of a disciple of Asmodeus of 6th level or higher, all evil-aligned creatures within 50 feet that have fewer Hit Dice than the disciple must succeed at a Will saving throw (DC 10 + disciple's class level + disciple's Cha bonus) or recognize the disciple as their superior. Affected creatures do not attack the disciple of Asmodeus and do as he commands as though affected by a mass suggestion spell. This mind-affecting ability lasts for 24 hours.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													BONUS:VAR|EvilAuthorityPerDay|1	BONUS:VAR|EvilAuthorityDC|DiscipleOfAsmodeusEvilAuthorityLVL												SOURCEPAGE:p.58	BONUS:VAR|DiscipleOfAsmodeusEvilAuthorityLVL|DiscipleOfAsmodeusLVL
Summon Major Devil			KEY:Disciple of Asmodeus ~ Summon Major Devil				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Disciple of Asmodeus Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:Once per week, a 8th-level disciple of Asmodeus can produce an effect identical to that of a greater planar ally spell to call a devil and work out a bargain for aid.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.58	BONUS:VAR|SummonMajorDevilPerDay|1
Greater Command				KEY:Disciple of Asmodeus ~ Greater Command				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Disciple of Asmodeus Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:Once per day, a 9th-level disciple of Asmodeus can produce an effect identical to that of a greater command spell cast by a spellcaster of his effective caster level.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.58	BONUS:VAR|GreaterCommandPerDay|1	BONUS:VAR|GreaterCommandLVL|DiscipleOfAsmodeusLVL
Dread Might					KEY:Disciple of Asmodeus ~ Dread Might					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Disciple of Asmodeus Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:Drawing some of Asmodeus's power into himself, the disciple gains a permanent +2 divine bonus to Armor Class and on saving throws and attack rolls.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.58

# Disciple of Baalzebul
Weapon and Armor Proficiency		KEY:Disciple of Baalzebul ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Disciple of Baalzebul Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						DESC:Disciples of Baalzebul are proficient with all simple and martial weapons, all light armors, but no shields.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.59
Tongue of the Devil			KEY:Disciple of Baalzebul ~ Tongue of the Devil				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Disciple of Baalzebul Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:A disciple of Baalzebul can speak with eloquence and believability, even when telling boldfaced lies, by using her cunning as well as her charm. When making Bluff checks, a disciple of Baalzebul adds her Intelligence modifier as well as her Charisma modifier to determine her check result.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.59
Sneak Attack				KEY:Disciple of Baalzebul ~ Sneak Attack					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Disciple of Baalzebul Class Feature.SpecialQuality				DEFINE:DiscipleOfBaalzebulSneakAttackLVL|0											DESC:If a disciple of Baalzebul of 2nd level or higher can catch an opponent when he is unable to defend himself effectively from her attack, she can strike a vital spot for extra damage. Basically, any time the disciple's target would be denied his Dexterity bonus to AC (whether he actually has a Dexterity bonus or not), the disciple's attack deals +1d6 points of damage. This extra damage increases by +1d6 points every third level afterward (+2d6 at 5th level, +3d6 at 8th level). Should the disciple score a critical hit with a sneak attack, this extra damage is not multiplied. It takes precision and penetration to hit a vital spot, so ranged attacks can only count as sneak attacks if the target is 30 feet away or less. With a sap or an unarmed strike, a disciple of Baalzebul can make a sneak attack that deals subdual damage instead of normal damage. She cannot use a weapon that deals normal damage to deal subdual damage in a sneak attack, not even with the usual -4 penalty, because she must make optimal use of her weapon in order to execute the sneak attack. A disciple of Baalzebul can only sneak attack a living creatures with a discernible anatomy-undead, constructs, oozes, plants, and incorporeal creatures lack vital areas to attack. Additionally, any creature immune to critical hits is similarly immune to sneak attacks. Also, the disciple of Baalzebul must be able to see the target well enough to pick out a vital spot and must be able to reach a vital spot. The disciple cannot sneak attack while striking at a creature with concealment or by striking the limbs of a creature whose vitals are beyond reach. If a disciple of Baalzebul gets a sneak attack bonus from another source (such as rogue levels), the bonuses to damage stack.																																																																																																																																																								BONUS:VAR|SneakAttackDice|(DiscipleOfBaalzebulSneakAttackLVL+1)/3																		SOURCEPAGE:p.59	BONUS:VAR|DiscipleOfBaalzebulSneakAttackLVL|DiscipleOfBaalzebulLVL
Suggestion					KEY:Disciple of Baalzebul ~ Suggestion					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Disciple of Baalzebul Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:Once per day, a 3rd-level disciple of Baalzebul can produce an effect identical to that of a suggestion spell. The DC to resist the disciple's entreaties is 10 + disciple's class level + disciple's Cha bonus.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																				BONUS:DC|SPELL.Suggestion|CL-3	BONUS:VAR|SuggestionPerDay|1																								SOURCEPAGE:p.59	BONUS:VAR|SuggestionLVL|DiscipleOfBaalzebulLVL
Summon Osyluth				KEY:Disciple of Baalzebul ~ Summon Osyluth				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Disciple of Baalzebul Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:A 4th-level disciple of Baalzebul can summon 1 osyluth once per day. This functions as a summon monster spell cast by a 15th-level caster.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																						BONUS:VAR|SummonOsyluthPerDay|1																							SOURCEPAGE:p.59
Insect Plague				KEY:Disciple of Baalzebul ~ Insect Plague					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Disciple of Baalzebul Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:Once per day, a 6th-level disciple of Baalzebul can produce an effect identical to that of a insect plague spell cast by a 15th-level spellcaster. The insects summoned are always biting flies.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													BONUS:VAR|InsectPlaguePerDay|1	BONUS:VAR|InsectPlagueLVL|15																		SOURCEPAGE:p.59
Beguiling Nature				KEY:Disciple of Baalzebul ~ Beguiling Nature				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Disciple of Baalzebul Class Feature.SpecialQuality		DEFINE:DiscipleOfBaalzebulBeguilingNatureLVL|0											DESC:Every other day, a 7th-level disciple of Baalzebul can produce an effect identical to the mass charm spell, with aWill save DC of 10 + disciple's class level + disciple's Cha bonus.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																														BONUS:VAR|BeguilingNaturePerDay|1	BONUS:VAR|BeguilingNatureDC|DiscipleOfBaalzebulBeguilingNatureLVL												SOURCEPAGE:p.59	BONUS:VAR|DiscipleOfBaalzebulBeguilingNatureLVL|DiscipleOfBaalzebulLVL
Summon Cornugon				KEY:Disciple of Baalzebul ~ Summon Cornugon				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Disciple of Baalzebul Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:A 9th-level disciple of Baalzebul can summon 1 cornugon once per day. This functions as a summon monster spell cast by a 15th-level caster.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																					BONUS:VAR|SummonCornugonPerDay|1																							SOURCEPAGE:p.59
King of Lies				KEY:Disciple of Baalzebul ~ King of Lies					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Disciple of Baalzebul Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:A 10th-level disciple of Baalzebul gains a +4 inherent bonus to Charisma.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.59

# Disciple of Dispater
Weapon and Armor Proficiency		KEY:Disciple of Dispater ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Disciple of Dispater Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						DESC:Disciples of Dispater are proficient with all simple and martial weapons, with all types of armor, and with shields.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																															ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|TYPE=ArmorProfHeavy|TYPE=ShieldProfTower|TYPE=WeaponProfMartial																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.60
Device Lore					KEY:Disciple of Dispater ~ Device Lore					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Disciple of Dispater Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:A disciple of Dispater can find traps made mostly of metal just as a rogue can. Furthermore, he gains a +2 competency bonus on Disable Device checks against devices made mostly of metal.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.60	ASPECT:SkillBonus|+2 competency bonus on Disable Device checks against devices made mostly of metal.
Iron Hews					KEY:Disciple of Dispater ~ Iron Hews					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Disciple of Dispater Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:Once per day per point of Constitution bonus, a 2nd-level disciple of Dispater may add a +3 divine bonus on damage from attacks made that round.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																					BONUS:VAR|IronHewsTimes|CON																								SOURCEPAGE:p.60	ASPECT:NAME|Ironhews %1/day|IronHewsTimes
Rusting Grasp				KEY:Disciple of Dispater ~ Rusting Grasp					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Disciple of Dispater Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:Once per day, a 3rd-level disciple of Dispater can produce an effect identical to that of the rusting grasp spell cast by a 15th-level caster.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																											ABILITY:Spell-Like Ability|AUTOMATIC|Rusting Grasp																		BONUS:VAR|RustingGraspTimes|1	BONUS:VAR|RustingGraspLVL|15																			SOURCEPAGE:p.60
Iron Power					KEY:Disciple of Dispater ~ Iron Power					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Disciple of Dispater Class Feature.SpecialQuality		DEFINE:DiscipleOfDispaterIronPowerLVL|0												DESC:When using an iron or steel weapon, a 4th-level disciple of Dispater gains a +1 insight bonus on attack and damage rolls. Furthermore, his threat range is doubled as if he were using a keen weapon. At 8th level, the insight bonus improves to +2, and the threat range triples. This ability does not stack with the keen weapon quality, but it does stack with the Improved Critical feat.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													BONUS:VAR|IronPowerBonus|DiscipleOfDispaterIronPowerLVL/4																			SOURCEPAGE:p.60	ASPECT:NAME|Iron Power +%1|IronPowerBonus		BONUS:VAR|DiscipleOfDispaterIronPowerLVL|DiscipleOfDispaterLVL
Summon Erinyes				KEY:Disciple of Dispater ~ Summon Erinyes					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Disciple of Dispater Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:A 5th-level disciple of Dispater can summon 1 erinyes once per day. This functions as a summon monster spell cast by a 15th-level caster. A 9th-level disciple of Dispater can summon 1d4 erinyes once per day.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																ABILITY:Spell-Like Ability|AUTOMATIC|Summon Erinyes																		BONUS:VAR|SummonErinyesTimes|1																							SOURCEPAGE:p.60
Greater Iron Hews				KEY:Disciple of Dispater ~ Greater Iron Hews				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Disciple of Dispater Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:Once per day per point of Constitution bonus, a 6th-level disciple of Dispater may add a +6 divine bonus on damage from attacks made that round. While this bonus does not stack with the iron hews ability, the abilities are separate: A disciple of Dispater with a Constitution bonus of +3 can use each ability three times per day.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																						BONUS:VAR|GreaterIronHewsTimes|CON																							SOURCEPAGE:p.60	ASPECT:NAME|Greater Iron Hews %1/Day|GreaterIronHewsTimes
Ironskin					KEY:Disciple of Dispater ~ Ironskin						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Disciple of Dispater Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:Once per day, a 7th-level disciple of Dispater can produce an effect identical to that of the stoneskin spell cast by a 15th-level caster upon himself only.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									ABILITY:Spell-Like Ability|AUTOMATIC|Ironskin																			BONUS:VAR|IronskinTimes|1	BONUS:VAR|IronskinLVL|15																			SOURCEPAGE:p.60
Iron Body					KEY:Disciple of Dispater ~ Iron Body					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Disciple of Dispater Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:Once per day, a 10th-level disciple of Dispater can produce an effect identical to that of an iron body spell cast by an 18th-level caster.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																											ABILITY:Spell-Like Ability|AUTOMATIC|Iron Body																			BONUS:VAR|IronBodyTimes|1	BONUS:VAR|IronBodyLVL|18																			SOURCEPAGE:p.60

# Disciple of Mammon
Weapon and Armor Proficiency		KEY:Disciple of Mammon ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Disciple of Mammon Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						DESC:Disciples ofMammon are proficient with all simple and martial weapons, but no type of armor or shields.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.61
Lie						KEY:Disciple of Mammon ~ Lie							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Disciple of Mammon Class Feature.SpecialQuality		DEFINE:DiscipleOfMammonLieLVL|0													DESC:A disciple of Mammon gains a +4 competence bonus on Bluff checks and spell resistance of 11 + disciple level against spells that reveal falsehood, such as zone of truth and discern lies, even when spell resistance is normally not allowed (such as with discern lies).																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																BONUS:VAR|LieSR|DiscipleOfMammonLieLVL																						SOURCEPAGE:p.61	BONUS:VAR|DiscipleOfMammonLieLVL|DiscipleOfMammonLVL
Cheat						KEY:Disciple of Mammon ~ Cheat						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Disciple of Mammon Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:Once per day per class level, a disciple of Mammon can produce an effect identical to that of a cheat spell cast by a 15th-level caster.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																						BONUS:VAR|CheatLVL|15																									SOURCEPAGE:p.61	BONUS:VAR|CheatPerDay|DiscipleOfMammonLVL
Thief						KEY:Disciple of Mammon ~ Thief						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Disciple of Mammon Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:A 3rd-level disciple of Mammon gains a +4 competence bonus on Pick Pocket and Open Lock checks.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.61
Steal						KEY:Disciple of Mammon ~ Steal						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Disciple of Mammon Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:A 3rd-level disciple of Mammon can call a single unattended object weighing no more than 5 pounds to her as if using telekinesis. This functions as the spell cast by a 15th-level caster.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																														BONUS:VAR|StealPerDay|1	BONUS:VAR|StealLVL|15																					SOURCEPAGE:p.61
Divert Attack				KEY:Disciple of Mammon ~ Divert Attack					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Disciple of Mammon Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:Three times per day, a 4th-level disciple of Mammon can maneuver events so that an opponent's melee attack meant for her is actually directed at another character within the attacker's reach. The new target must also be a foe of the attacker. If there is no such foe within reach, the maneuver fails.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																											BONUS:VAR|DivertAttackPerDay|3																							SOURCEPAGE:p.61
Summon Osyluth				KEY:Disciple of Mammon ~ Summon Osyluth					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Disciple of Mammon Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:A 5th-level disciple of Mammon can summon 1 osyluth once per day. This functions as a summon monster spell cast by a 15th-level caster.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																						BONUS:VAR|SummonOsyluthPerDay|1																							SOURCEPAGE:p.61
Take Object					KEY:Disciple of Mammon ~ Take Object					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Disciple of Mammon Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:A 6th-level disciple of Mammon gains a +4 competence bonus on attempts to disarm a foe, and she draws no attacks of opportunity for making an attempt unarmed.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.61
Enhance Value				KEY:Disciple of Mammon ~ Enhance Value					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Disciple of Mammon Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:By careful, slight modifications, a 7th-level disciple of Mammon can increase the value of a nonmagical item of value, such as a gem, an art object, or a piece of equipment. The disciple spends 1 hour performing these modifications and then makes an Appraise check, increasing the value of the object by 1%% per point of the check result. A disciple of Mammon cannot enhance something with a readily obvious value, such as a coin, and she cannot enhance the same object twice.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.61
Divert Spell				KEY:Disciple of Mammon ~ Divert Spell					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Disciple of Mammon Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:Once per day, an 8th-level disciple of Mammon can maneuver events so that an opponent's spell targeted on her is actually targeted at another instead. The new target must be within range and must also be a foe of the attacker. If there is no such foe within reach, the maneuver fails.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													BONUS:VAR|DivertAttackPerDay|1																							SOURCEPAGE:p.61
Nondetection				KEY:Disciple of Mammon ~ Nondetection					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Disciple of Mammon Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:A 9th-level disciple of Mammon can constantly produce an effect identical to a nondetection spell cast by an 18th-level caster. This ability cannot be dispelled, but it can be suppressed.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.61
Summon Gelugon				KEY:Disciple of Mammon ~ Summon Gelugon					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Disciple of Mammon Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:A 10th-level disciple of Mammon can summon 1 gelugon once per day. This functions as a summon monster spell cast by an 18th-level caster.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																						BONUS:VAR|SummonGelugonPerDay|1																							SOURCEPAGE:p.61

# Disciple of Mephistopheles
Weapon and Armor Proficiency		KEY:Disciple of Mephistopheles ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Disciple of Mephistopheles Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:Disciples ofMephistopheles are proficient with all simple and martial weapons, with all types of armor, and with shields.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																				SOURCEPAGE:p.62
Hellfire Grasp				KEY:Disciple of Mephistopheles ~ Hellfire Grasp				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Disciple of Mephistopheles Class Feature.SpecialQuality																			DESC:A disciple of Mephistopheles can deal 1d6 points of fire damage as a touch attack at will. This damage is added to damage dealt by other unarmed attacks.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																			BONUS:VAR|HellfireGrasp|1																								SOURCEPAGE:p.62
Fire Adept					KEY:Disciple of Mephistopheles ~ Fire Adept				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Disciple of Mephistopheles Class Feature.SpecialQuality																			DESC:A disciple of Mephistopheles who can cast spells gains a +1 bonus to caster level when casting a spell with the fire descriptor.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.62
Fire Resistance				KEY:Disciple of Mephistopheles ~ Fire Resistance			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Disciple of Mephistopheles Class Feature.SpecialQuality																			DESC:At 2nd level, a disciple of Mephistopheles gains fire resistance 10. At 6th level, this becomes fire resistance 20.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.62	BONUS:VAR|FireResistanceBonus|10*(DiscipleOfMephistophelesLVL>=2)+(DiscipleOfMephistophelesLVL>=5)
Hellfire Blast				KEY:Disciple of Mephistopheles ~ Hellfire Blast				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Disciple of Mephistopheles Class Feature.SpecialQuality																			DESC:A 3rd-level disciple of Mephistopheles can release a gout of hellfire from his hand at will, dealing 4d6 points of fire damage as a ranged touch attack. The range for this attack is 30 feet.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													BONUS:VAR|HellfireBlast|4																								SOURCEPAGE:p.62
Flare						KEY:Disciple of Mephistopheles ~ Flare					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Disciple of Mephistopheles Class Feature.SpecialQuality																			DESC:Once per day per class level, a disciple of Mephistopheles can produce an effect identical to that of a flare spell cast by a 15th-level caster.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.62	BONUS:VAR|FlarePerDay|DiscipleOfMephistophelesLVL	BONUS:VAR|FlareLVL|15
Summon Hamatula				KEY:Disciple of Mephistopheles ~ Summon Hamatula			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Disciple of Mephistopheles Class Feature.SpecialQuality																			DESC:A 5th-level disciple ofMephistopheles can summon 1 hamatula once per day. This functions as a summon monster spell cast by a 15th-level caster. A 9th-level disciple can summon 1d4 hamatulas once per day.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.62	BONUS:VAR|SummonHamatulaPerDay|1
Hellfire					KEY:Disciple of Mephistopheles ~ Hellfire					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Disciple of Mephistopheles Class Feature.SpecialQuality																			DESC:Three times per day, a 6th-level disciple of Mephistopheles can produce an effect identical to that of a hellfire spell cast by a 15th-level caster.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.62	BONUS:VAR|HellfirePerDay|3	BONUS:VAR|HellfireLVL|15
Fire Shield					KEY:Disciple of Mephistopheles ~ Fire Shield				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Disciple of Mephistopheles Class Feature.SpecialQuality																			DESC:Twice per day, a 7th-level disciple of Mephistopheles can produce an effect identical to that of a fire shield spell cast by a 15th-level caster.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.62	BONUS:VAR|FireShieldPerDay|2	BONUS:VAR|FireShieldLVL|15
Hellfire Storm				KEY:Disciple of Mephistopheles ~ Hellfire Storm				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Disciple of Mephistopheles Class Feature.SpecialQuality																			DESC:Twice per day, an 8th-level disciple of Mephistopheles can produce an effect identical to that of the hellfire storm spell cast by a 15th-level caster.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.63	BONUS:VAR|HellfireStormPerDay|2	BONUS:VAR|HellfireStormLVL|15
Body of Flame				KEY:Disciple of Mephistopheles ~ Body of Flame				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Disciple of Mephistopheles Class Feature.SpecialQuality																			DESC:A 10th-level disciple of Mephistopheles can transform his body into flame for up to 10 minutes once per day. He gains fire immunity and damage reduction 30/+1, and anyone he touches must succeed at a Reflex save (DC 15) or catch fire. The flame burns for 1d4 rounds (see Catching on Fire in Chapter 3 of the DUNGEON MASTER's Guide). A burning creature can take a move-equivalent action to put out the flame. Creatures hitting a disciple ofMephistopheles with natural weapons or unarmed attacks take 2d6 points of fire damage and also catch fire unless they succeed at a Reflex save (DC 15).																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.63	BONUS:VAR|BodyOfFlamePerDay|1	BONUS:VAR|BodyOfFlameDuration|10

# Lifedrinker
Weapon and Armor Proficiency		KEY:Lifedrinker ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Lifedrinker Class Feature.SpecialQuality																								DESC:A lifedrinker is proficient with no weapons, armor, or shields.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.63
Lifewell					KEY:Lifedrinker ~ Lifewell							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Lifedrinker Class Feature.SpecialQuality			DEFINE:LifedrinkerLifewellLVL|0													DESC:A lifedrinker stores the life energy that it steals in a reservoir within itself called a lifewell. From this lifewell, the lifedrinker draws the power needed to use their its abilities. A lifedrinker gains lifewell points by bestowing negative levels and by dealing Constitution drain. Each negative level bestowed by the vampire's energy drain ability grants 2 lifewell points. Each point of Constitution drained grants 1 lifewell point. The lifewell of a lifedrinker can hold a maximum of 3 points per lifedrinker level. Lifewell points gained when the lifewell is already full are wasted. A lifedrinker with 0 lifewell points must succeed at aWill saving throw (DC 20) or go temporarily insane, attacking any living creature within sight until the lifewell has at least 1 point per lifedrinker level. A successful saving throw means that the lifedrinker need not make a saving throw against this temporary insanity until one week has passed- and even then only if the lifewell has remained at 0 points throughout the week.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																		BONUS:VAR|Lifewell|3*LifedrinkerLifewellLVL																					SOURCEPAGE:p.63	BONUS:VAR|LifedrinkerLifewellLVL|LifedrinkerLVL
Invigorate					KEY:Lifedrinker ~ Invigorate							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Lifedrinker Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:A lifedrinker can spend 1 lifewell point to gain 1d6 temporary hit points. These hit points last 24 hours, and while they do not stack with those granted by other sources of temporary hit points, they do stack with more hit points gained from the invigorate ability, so a lifedrinker may spend multiple lifewell points to gain more temporary hit points.No more lifewell points may be spent on this ability in any given day than the lifedrinker has levels.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.63
Spell Boost (Empower)			KEY:Lifedrinker ~ Spell Boost (Empower)					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Lifedrinker Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:If a lifedrinker of 2nd level or higher casts spells, it may spend 4 lifewell points to empower a spell as if using the Empower Spell feat. The spell slot and level of the spell do not change.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.63
Spell Boost (Heighten)			KEY:Lifedrinker ~ Spell Boost (Heighten)					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Lifedrinker Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:If a lifedrinker of 3rd level or higher casts spells, it may spend a variable number of lifewell points to heighten a spell as if using the Heighten Spell feat. For every 2 lifewell points devoted to the spell boost, the spell's effective level is treated as one higher for purposes of save DC and other effects. For example, if a lifedrinker spends 4 lifewell points to boost a fireball spell, the spell is treated as a 5th-level spell when calculating the Reflex save DC, and the boosted fireball can penetrate a minor globe of invulnerability, which a 3rd-level fireball cannot. The spell slot and level of the spell do not change.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.63
Special Attack Boost (Empower)	KEY:Lifedrinker ~ Special Attack Boost (Empower)			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Lifedrinker Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:A 4th-level lifedrinker can spend 4 lifewell points to empower a special attack, increasing its variable, numeric effects by a factor of 1.5. The special attack is empowered for one use only. For example, a lifedrinker empowering its blood drain ability would drain 1d3 points of Constitution, multiplied by 1.5. A lifedrinker could also use this ability to summon more creatures using the children of the night ability it gains as a vampire. Some lifedrinkers might have other special abilities that they can use with this ability; a sea hag vampire lifedrinker, for example, could use this to empower her horrific appearance.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.64
Special Attack Boost (Heighten)	KEY:Lifedrinker ~ Special Attack Boost (Heighten)			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Lifedrinker Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:A 4th-level lifedrinker can spend a variable number of lifewell points to heighten a special attack, as if using the Heighten Spell feat. The special attack is heightened for one use only. For every 2 lifewell points devoted to the special attack, the special attack's effective level is treated as one higher for purposes of save DC and other effects.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.64
Blood Servant				KEY:Lifedrinker ~ Blood Servant						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Lifedrinker Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:By spending 10 lifewell points, a 5th-level lifedrinker can call forth a lesser planar ally (evil only), as per the spell of the same name. The ally automatically serves the lifedrinker for 24 hours.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.64
Boost Defenses				KEY:Lifedrinker ~ Boost Defenses						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Lifedrinker Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:At 5th level, a lifedrinker can spend 8 lifewell points to add +2 to its natural armor bonus and turn resistance, add +10 to its cold resistance and electricity resistance, and increase its damage reduction to 20/+2. The effects last for 24 hours.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.64
Spell Boost (Maximize)			KEY:Lifedrinker ~ Spell Boost (Maximize)					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Lifedrinker Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:If a lifedrinker of 6th level or higher casts spells, it can spend 6 lifewell points to maximize a spell as if using theMaximize Spell feat.The spell slot and level of the spell do not change.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.64
Greater Blood Drain			KEY:Lifedrinker ~ Greater Blood Drain					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Lifedrinker Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:At 7th level, a lifedrinker's blood drain ability now deals 1d6 points of Constitution drain.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.64
Special Attack Boost (Maximize)	KEY:Lifedrinker ~ Special Attack Boost (Maximize)			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Lifedrinker Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:A lifedrinker of 7th level or higher can spend 6 lifewell points to maximize all variable, numeric effects of a special attack. The special attack is maximized for one use only. A lifedrinker using this ability to maximize its greater blood drain ability, for example, would deal 6 points of Constitution drain. A lifedrinker could also use this ability to summon the maximum number of creatures using the children of the night ability it gains as a vampire. Some lifedrinkers might have other special abilities that they can boost in a similar fashion.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.64
Spell Boost (Quicken)			KEY:Lifedrinker ~ Spell Boost (Quicken)					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Lifedrinker Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:If a lifedrinker of 8th level or higher casts spells, it can spend 8 lifewell points to quicken one of its spells, as if using the Quicken Spell feat. The spell slot and level of the spell do not change.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.64
Greater Invigorate			KEY:Lifedrinker ~ Greater Invigorate					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Lifedrinker Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:Whenever a 9th-level lifedrinker uses its invigorate ability, it gains a +1 enhancement bonus to Strength for each lifewell point spent. If multiple lifewell points are spent at the same time, the bonus is correspondingly larger. A lifedrinker that spends 10 lifewell points all at once on invigorate gains 10d6 temporary hit points and a +10 enhancement bonus to Strength. But if the lifedrinker spends 5 lifewell points in one round and 5 more points in the next, it has 10d6 temporary hit points but only a +5 enhancement bonus to Strength.The bonus to Strength lasts for 24 hours.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.64
Blood Revel					KEY:Lifedrinker ~ Blood Revel							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Lifedrinker Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:Once a 10th-level lifedrinker drains any blood from a victim, it can choose to enter a state called a blood revel as a free action at the beginning of its next turn and remain in that state for 10 rounds. In this state, the lifedrinker gains a +4 profane bonus to Strength, its damage reduction increases to 25/+3, its fast healing increases to 10 points per round, and it may ignore its weakness toward garlic, mirrors, holy symbols, and running water, as well as its vulnerability to sunlight. However, during the blood revel, the lifedrinker cannot flee from a living foe, and must attack physically every round. A hasted lifedrinker in a blood revel could use its extra partial action to cast a spell as long as it also made a melee attack that round. A blood revel ends when the lifedrinker chooses it to end, when 10 rounds are over, or when no living foes can be reached by a full attack, a move and an attack, or a charge. When the blood revel ends, the lifedrinker must reach its coffin home within 2 hours or be utterly destroyed, as if it were reduced to 0 hit points. It must remain in its coffin for as long as it was in its revel, plus the amount of time it took to reach its coffin.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.64

# Mortal Hunter
Weapon and Armor Proficiency		KEY:Mortal Hunter ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Mortal Hunter Class Feature.SpecialQuality																							DESC:Mortal hunters are proficient with no weapons, armor, or shields.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.65
Spells					KEY:Mortal Hunter ~ Spells							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Mortal Hunter Class Feature.SpecialQuality																							DESC:A mortal hunter gains the ability to cast a small number of arcane spells. To cast a spell, the mortal hunter must have a Charisma score of at least 10 + the spell's level, so a mortal hunter with a Charisma of 10 or lower cannot cast these spells. Mortal hunter bonus spells are based on Charisma, and saving throws against these spells have a DC of 10 + spell level + Cha modifier.When Table 5-10 shows 0 spells of a given level, such as 0 1st-level spells at 1st level, the mortal hunter gets only bonus spells. A mortal hunter without a bonus spell for that level cannot yet cast a spell of that level. The mortal hunter's spell list appears below; it has access to any spell on the list and need not prepare those spells ahead of time, just as a sorcerer. A mortal hunter casts spells just as a sorcerer does.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.65
Mortal Hunting				KEY:Mortal Hunter ~ Mortal Hunting						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Mortal Hunter Class Feature.SpecialQuality			DEFINE:MortalHunterMortalHuntingLVL|0												DESC:A mortal hunter gains a bonus against mortals due to its extensive study of them and training in the proper combat techniques. The mortal hunter gains a +1 bonus on attack and damage rolls against mortals and the same bonus on Bluff, Listen, Sense Motive, Spot, and Wilderness Lore checks when using these skills against mortals. The damage bonus applies to ranged weapons only against targets within 30 feet (the mortal hunter cannot strike with deadly accuracy beyond that range). The bonus does not apply to damage against creatures that are immune to critical hits. At 3rd, 6th, and 9th level, the mortal hunter's bonus associated with mortals goes up by +1. This bonus stacks with a ranger's favored enemy bonus.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																					BONUS:VAR|MortalHuntingBonus|(MortalHunterMortalHuntingLVL+3)/3																		SOURCEPAGE:p.65	BONUS:VAR|MortalHunterMortalHuntingLVL|MortalHunterLVL
Mortal Skin					KEY:Mortal Hunter ~ Mortal Skin						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Mortal Hunter Class Feature.SpecialQuality			DEFINE:MortalHunterMortalSkinLVL|0													DESC:By magically grafting bits of mortal flesh to its own body, a mortal hunter gains the ability at 1st level to transform (as the polymorph self spell) into any humanoid mortal form. At 5th level, a mortal hunter can polymorph into any mortal form except that of a dragon. At 8th level, any mortal form can be adopted. If the flesh used is from the exact individual being imitated, the duration is permanent. If the flesh is from a being of the same type as the form adopted, the duration is 1 hour. If the flesh is not the same type as the form adopted, the duration is 10 minutes. In all cases, the mortal hunter can dismiss the ability as a standard action. Otherwise, this ability works as the polymorph self spell, and the mortal hunter can call upon it once per day.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																												BONUS:VAR|MortalSkinPower|(MortalHunterMortalSkinLVL+5)/5	BONUS:VAR|MortalSkinPerDay|1														SOURCEPAGE:p.65	BONUS:VAR|MortalHunterMortalSkinLVL|MortalHunterLVL
Detect Mortals				KEY:Mortal Hunter ~ Detect Mortals						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Mortal Hunter Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:A 2nd-level mortal hunter can use detect mortals at will. This ability duplicates the effect of detect undead cast by a 15th-level caster, except that mortals are detected.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.65
Boost Spell-Like Ability		KEY:Mortal Hunter ~ Boost Spell-Like Ability				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Mortal Hunter Class Feature.SpecialQuality																							DESC:At 2nd level, a mortal hunter gains this feat as a bonus feat.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.65
Smite Mortals				KEY:Mortal Hunter ~ Smite Mortals						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Mortal Hunter Class Feature.SpecialQuality			DEFINE:MortalHunterSmiteMortalsLVL|0												DESC:Once per day, a mortal hunter of 4th level or higher may attempt to smite mortals with one normal melee attack. It adds itsWisdom modifier (if positive) to its attack roll and deals 2 extra points of damage per class level; for example, an 8th-level mortal hunter armed with a longsword would deal 1d8+16 points of damage, plus 3 points of damage for its mortal hunting ability, plus any additional bonuses for high Strength or magical effects. If the mortal hunter accidentally smites a creature that is not a mortal, the smite has no effect but is still used up for that day.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																												BONUS:VAR|SmiteMortals|1	BONUS:VAR|SmiteMortalsToHit|max(WIS,0)	BONUS:VAR|SmiteMortalsDamage|2*MortalHunterSmiteMortalsLVL							SOURCEPAGE:p.65	BONUS:VAR|MortalHunterSmiteMortalsLVL|MortalHunterLVL
Spurn Mortal Magic			KEY:Mortal Hunter ~ Spurn Mortal Magic					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Mortal Hunter Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:A 5th-level mortal hunter applies its Wisdom modifier (if positive) as an additional bonus on all saving throws against spells and spell-like abilities used by mortals. Will saving throws thus add double the normal Wisdom modifier.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																						BONUS:VAR|SpurnMortalMagicBonus|max(WIS,0)																					SOURCEPAGE:p.65
Claws of the Overfiend			KEY:Mortal Hunter ~ Claws of the Overfiend				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Mortal Hunter Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:At 7th level, the damage dealt by all of the mortal hunter's natural attacks increases by one step.Use the table in the Size Increases section in the introduction of the Monster Manual to determine the proper die increase. For example, a bite that deals 1d6+2 points of damage now deals 1d8+2 points of damage.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.65
Mortalbane Shout				KEY:Mortal Hunter ~ Mortalbane Shout					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Mortal Hunter Class Feature.SpecialQuality			DEFINE:MortalHunterMortalbaneShoutLVL|0												DESC:An 8th-level mortal hunter can, once per day, give a shout that stuns for 1 round all mortals within 50 feet who fail a Fortitude save (DC 10 + Charisma bonus + class levels).																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																															BONUS:VAR|MortalbanePerDay|1	BONUS:VAR|MortalbaneDC|MortalHunterMortalbaneShoutLVL															SOURCEPAGE:p.65	BONUS:VAR|MortalHunterMortalbaneShoutLVL|MortalHunterLVL
Slay Mortal					KEY:Mortal Hunter ~ Slay Mortal						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Mortal Hunter Class Feature.SpecialQuality			DEFINE:MortalHunterSlayMortalLVL|0													DESC:A 10th-level mortal hunter can attempt to slay a mortal with its touch once per day. If the mortal hunter succeeds at a melee touch attack, the mortal must make a Fortitude saving throw (DC 10 + class level + mortal hunter's Cha modifier) or die instantly.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																		BONUS:VAR|SlayMortalPerDay|1	BONUS:VAR|SlayMortalDC|MortalHunterSlayMortalLVL															SOURCEPAGE:p.65

# Soul Eater
Weapon and Armor Proficiency		KEY:Soul Eater ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Soul Eater Class Feature.SpecialQuality																								DESC:Soul eaters are proficient with no weapons, armor, or shields.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.66
Energy Drain				KEY:Soul Eater ~ Energy Drain							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Soul Eater Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						DESC:A soul eater gains the ability to drain energy, bestowing negative levels upon its victims. Beginning at 1st level, the touch of a soul eater bestows one negative level on its target. At 7th level, the soul eater bestows two negative levels with a touch.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.66	BONUS:VAR|EnergyDrainLevels|(SoulEaterLVL+5)/6
Soul Strength				KEY:Soul Eater ~ Soul Strength						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Soul Eater Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						DESC:When a 2nd-level soul eater uses its energy drain ability, it gains a +4 enhancement bonus to Strength for 24 hours.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.66
Soul Blast					KEY:Soul Eater ~ Soul Blast							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Soul Eater Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						DESC:When a 3rd-level soul eater uses its energy drain ability, it may project a 100-foot ray of force that deals 1d6 points of damage per soul eater level against one target. The target is allowed aReflex saving throwto avoid the damage (DC 10 + soul eater's class level + soul eater's Cha bonus). This supernatural ability can be used once per day, and only on a daywhen the soul eater has drained levels.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.66	BONUS:VAR|SoulBlastPerDay|1	BONUS:VAR|SoulBlastDamage|SoulEaterLVL	BONUS:VAR|SoulBlastDC|SoulEaterLVL
Soul Enhancement				KEY:Soul Eater ~ Soul Enhancement						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Soul Eater Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						DESC:When a 4th-level soul eater uses its energy drain ability, it gains a +2 enhancement bonus on all saving throws, ability checks, and skill checks for 24 hours. This bonus stacks with any enhancement bonuses gained to ability scores that apply to saves or checks.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.67
Soul Endurance				KEY:Soul Eater ~ Soul Endurance						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Soul Eater Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						DESC:When a 5th-level soul eater uses its energy drain ability, it gains a +4 enhancement bonus to Constitution for 24 hours.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.67
Soul Radiance				KEY:Soul Eater ~ Soul Radiance						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Soul Eater Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						DESC:If a 6th-level soul eater completely drains a creature of energy, it may adopt the creature's soul radiance, taking the victim's form, appearance, and abilities (as the shapechange spell) for 24 hours.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.67
Soul Agility				KEY:Soul Eater ~ Soul Agility							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Soul Eater Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						DESC:When an 8th-level soul eater uses its energy drain ability, it gains a +4 enhancement bonus to Dexterity for 24 hours.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.67
Soul Slave					KEY:Soul Eater ~ Soul Slave							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Soul Eater Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						DESC:If a 9th-level soul eater completely drains a creature of energy, the victim becomes a wight under the command of the soul eater.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.67
Soul Power					KEY:Soul Eater ~ Soul Power							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Soul Eater Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						DESC:After a 10th-level soul eater has drained energy, all spell-like and supernatural abilities gain a +2 profane bonus to their saving throw DC for 24 hours. Further, any and all spell-like or supernatural abilities the soul eater possesses may be used twice as often as normal during that 24-hour period. For example, if an aboleth soul eater drains energy, it may use its enslave power six times per day rather than three times per day.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.67

# Thrall of Demogorgon
Weapon and Armor Proficiency		KEY:Thrall of Demogorgon ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Thrall of Demogorgon Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						DESC:A thrall of Demogorgon is proficient with all simple and martial weapons, with all types of armor, and with shields.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.67
Bonus Feat or Spells			KEY:Thrall of Demogorgon ~ Bonus Feat or Spells				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Thrall of Demogorgon Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						DESC:When a thrall of Demogorgon attains 1st, 4th, 7th, and 10th level, the character gains new spells per day as if he had also gained a level in whatever spellcasting class he belonged to before he added the prestige class, or else he gains a bonus feat of his choice. If the thrall chooses +1 spellcasting level, he does not gain any other benefit a character of that class would have gained (improved chance of controlling or rebuking undead, metamagic or item creation feats, hit points beyond those received from the prestige class, and so on), except for an increased effective level of spellcasting. This essentially means that he adds the new level to the level of whatever other spellcasting class the character has, then determines spells per day, spells known, and caster level accordingly. If a character had more than one spellcasting class before he became a thrall ofDemogorgon, he must decide to which class he adds the level for purposes of determining spells per day. A thrall of Demogorgon is free to choose the bonus feat at one opportunity and the spellcasting level the next time the decision arises, or vice versa. Characters who are not spellcasters must choose the bonus feat.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.67	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Thrall of Demogorgon Ability|(ThrallOfDemogorgonLVL+2)/3
Scaly Flesh					KEY:Thrall of Demogorgon ~ Scaly Flesh					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Thrall of Demogorgon Class Feature.SpecialQuality		DEFINE:ThrallOfDemogorgonScalyFleshLVL|0												DESC:A 1st-level thrall of Demogorgon gains dark scaly flesh, which provides a +1 natural armor bonus. At every three levels beyond 1st (4th, 7th, and 10th), this bonus increases by +1. The bonus from scaly flesh stacks with that of natural armor derived from creature type (if the thrall of Demogorgon is a lizardfolk or troglodyte, for example), but not from magical sources such as an amulet of natural armor.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									BONUS:VAR|ScalyFleshAC|(ThrallOfDemogorgonScalyFleshLVL+2)/3																		SOURCEPAGE:p.68	BONUS:VAR|ThrallOfDemogorgonScalyFleshLVL|ThrallOfDemogorgonLVL
Hypnosis					KEY:Thrall of Demogorgon ~ Hypnosis						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Thrall of Demogorgon Class Feature.SpecialQuality		DEFINE:ThrallOfDemogorgonHypnosisLVL|0												DESC:Once per day, a thrall of Demogorgon can produce an effect identical to that of the hypnotism spell, except that it functions as a gaze attack with a range of 30 feet. The Will save DC to resist the effect is 10 + thrall's class level + thrall's Cha modifier.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																	BONUS:VAR|HypnosisPerDay|1	BONUS:VAR|HypnosisDC|ThrallOfDemogorgonHypnosisLVL															SOURCEPAGE:p.68	BONUS:VAR|ThrallOfDemogorgonHypnosisLVL|ThrallOfDemogorgonLVL
Touch of Fear				KEY:Thrall of Demogorgon ~ Touch of Fear					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Thrall of Demogorgon Class Feature.SpecialQuality		DEFINE:ThrallOfDemogorgonTouchOfFearLVL|0												DESC:Three times per day, a thrall of Demogorgon of 2nd level or higher can use an effect identical to that of the cause fear spell. The Will save DC to negate the fear is 10 + class level + Cha modifier.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																											BONUS:VAR|TouchOfFearPerDay|3	BONUS:VAR|TouchOfFearDC|ThrallOfDemogorgonTouchOfFearLVL														SOURCEPAGE:p.68	BONUS:VAR|ThrallOfDemogorgonTouchOfFearLVL|ThrallOfDemogorgonLVL
Reaching Touch				KEY:Thrall of Demogorgon ~ Reaching Touch					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Thrall of Demogorgon Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:Three times per day, a 3rd-level thrall of Demogorgon can cause his arms to stretch unnaturally like tentacles, providing him an extra 5 feet of reach for 1 round.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.68	BONUS:VAR|ReachingTouchPerDay|2
Dual Actions				KEY:Thrall of Demogorgon ~ Dual Actions					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Thrall of Demogorgon Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:Twice per day, a 4th-level thrall of Demogorgon can take two full rounds' worth of actions in the same round.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.68	BONUS:VAR|DualActionPerDay|2
Summon Demon				KEY:Thrall of Demogorgon ~ Summon Demon					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Thrall of Demogorgon Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:A 5th-level thrall of Demogorgon can summon a demon of 5 HD or less once per day. This functions as a summon monster spell cast by a 15th-level caster. Once per day, a 9th-level thrall of Demogorgon can summon a demon of 10 HD or less.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.68	BONUS:VAR|SummonDemonPerDay|1		BONUS:VAR|SummonMajorDemonPerDay|(ThrallOfDemogorgonLVL>=9)
Rotting Touch				KEY:Thrall of Demogorgon ~ Rotting Touch					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Thrall of Demogorgon Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:Three times per day, a thrall of Demogorgon can deal 1d6 points of Constitution damage as a touch attack.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.68	BONUS:VAR|RottingTouchPerDay|3
Two Personas				KEY:Thrall of Demogorgon ~ Two Personas					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Thrall of Demogorgon Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:An 8th-level thrall of Demogorgon goes a little insane, if he is not already mad. The thrall develops a multiple personality disorder that has the side effect of allowing the character to multiclass freely with no experience point penalties.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.68
Death Touch					KEY:Thrall of Demogorgon ~ Death Touch					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Thrall of Demogorgon Class Feature.SpecialQuality		DEFINE:ThrallOfDemogorgonDeathTouchLVL|0												DESC:At 8th level, a thrall of Demogorgon can use an effect identical to that of a slay living spell once per day. The Fortitude save DC to avoid death is 10 + class level + Cha modifier.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																														BONUS:VAR|DeathTouchPerDay|1	BONUS:VAR|DeathTouchDC|ThrallOfDemogorgonDeathTouchLVL														SOURCEPAGE:p.68	BONUS:VAR|ThrallOfDemogorgonDeathTouchLVL|ThrallOfDemogorgonLVL
Demogorgon's Will				KEY:Thrall of Demogorgon ~ Demogorgon's Will				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Thrall of Demogorgon Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:A 10th-level thrall of Demogorgon can call upon the power of his master and be granted a limited wish spell once per day. The use of this ability requires 3 full rounds devoted to entreaties and prayers to Demogorgon before the limited wish is granted. The thrall must pay the experience point cost and provide any needed material components.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.68	BONUS:VAR|DemogorgonSWillPerDay|1

# Thrall of Graz'zt
Weapon and Armor Proficiency		KEY:Thrall of Graz'zt ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Thrall of Graz'zt Class Feature.SpecialQuality																							DESC:Thralls of Graz'zt are proficient with no weapons, armor, or shields.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.68
Spells					KEY:Thrall of Graz'zt ~ Spells						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Thrall of Graz'zt Class Feature.SpecialQuality																							DESC:When a thrall of Graz'zt gains 1st level, and every two levels after that (plus 10th level), the character gains new spells per day as if she had also gained a level in whatever spellcasting class she belonged to before she added the prestige class. She does not, however, gain any other benefit a character of that class would have gained (improved chance of controlling or rebuking undead, metamagic or item creation feats, hit points beyond those received from the prestige class, and so on), except for an increased effective level of spellcasting. This essentially means that she adds the new level of thrall of Graz'zt to the level of whatever other spellcasting class the character has, then determines spells per day, spells known, and caster level accordingly. For example, if Kalleyis, an 8th-level wizard, gains a level in thrall of Graz'zt, she gains new spells as if she had risen to 9th level in wizard, but uses the other thrall of Graz'zt aspects of level progression such as base attack bonus and save bonus. If she next gains a level of wizard, making her a 9th-level wizard/1st-level thrall of Graz'zt, she gains spells as if she had risen to 10th-level wizard. If a character had more than one spellcasting class before she became a thrall of Graz'zt, she must decide to which class she adds the level of thrall of Graz'zt.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.68
Charm						KEY:Thrall of Graz'zt ~ Charm							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Thrall of Graz'zt Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:A thrall of Graz'zt can produce an effect identical to that of a charm person spell cast by a caster of the thrall of Graz'zt's class level.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.69	BONUS:VAR|CharmPersonPerDay|1	BONUS:VAR|CharmPersonLVL|ThrallOfGrazztLVL
Spell Betrayal				KEY:Thrall of Graz'zt ~ Spell Betrayal					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Thrall of Graz'zt Class Feature.SpecialQuality		DEFINE:ThrallOfGrazztSpellBetrayalLVL|0												DESC:When casting a damage-dealing spell at a target or targets denied their Dexterity bonus, a thrall of Graz'zt of 2nd level or higher can increase the amount of damage dealt. A 2nd-level thrall, for example, adds +1d6 points of damage to a spell cast against flatfooted targets. Graz'zt grants this ability in the hope that the thrall will convince her enemies that she is their friend, then betray them with a surprise magical attack. The damage increase goes up by +1d6 for every two levels beyond 2nd, to +5d6 at 10th level.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																					BONUS:VAR|SpellBetrayal|ThrallOfGrazztSpellBetrayalLVL/2																			SOURCEPAGE:p.69	BONUS:VAR|ThrallOfGrazztSpellBetrayalLVL|ThrallOfGrazztLVL
Dark Charisma				KEY:Thrall of Graz'zt ~ Dark Charisma					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Thrall of Graz'zt Class Feature.SpecialQuality		DEFINE:ThrallOfGrazztDarkCharismaLVL|0												DESC:At 3rd level, a thrall of Graz'zt can add an enhancement bonus on certain Charismabased skill checks. The bonus is +1 at 3rd level, +2 at 5th level, and +3 at 7th level. The bonus improves Animal Empathy, Diplomacy, Bluff, Gather Information, Handle Animal, and Perform checks when dealing with evil creatures.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									BONUS:VAR|DarkCharismaBonus|max(3,(ThrallOfGrazztDarkCharismaLVL-1)/2)																	SOURCEPAGE:p.69	BONUS:VAR|ThrallOfGrazztDarkCharismaLVL|ThrallOfGrazztLVL
Summon Demon				KEY:Thrall of Graz'zt ~ Summon Demon					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Thrall of Graz'zt Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:A 4th-level thrall of Graz'zt can summon a demon of 5HD or less once per day. This functions as a summon monster spell cast by a 15th-level caster. A 9th-level thrall of Graz'zt can summon a demon of 10 HD or less once per day.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.69	BONUS:VAR|SummonDemonPerDay|1		BONUS:VAR|SummonMajorDemonPerDay|(ThrallOfGrazztLVL>=8)
Spellstrike					KEY:Thrall of Graz'zt ~ Spellstrike						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Thrall of Graz'zt Class Feature.SpecialQuality		DEFINE:ThrallOfGrazztSpellstrikeLVL|0												DESC:If a thrall of Graz'zt casts a damaging spell upon a target or targets threatened in melee (and thus distracted), the thrall can add half of the spell betrayal bonus (round down) to the damage dealt. Thus, a 6th-level or 7th-level thrall of Graz'zt deals an additional +1d6 points of damage with a spell against threatened targets. At 8th level and higher, this bonus damage increases to +2d6 points.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																										BONUS:VAR|Spellstrike|1|PREVARGTEQ:6,ThrallOfGrazztSpellstrikeLVL	BONUS:VAR|Spellstrike|1|PREVARGTEQ:8,ThrallOfGrazztSpellstrikeLVL							SOURCEPAGE:p.69	BONUS:VAR|ThrallOfGrazztSpellstrikeLVL|ThrallOfGrazztLVL

# Thrall of Juiblex
Weapon and Armor Proficiency		KEY:Thrall of Juiblex ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Thrall of Juiblex Class Feature.SpecialQuality																							DESC:A thrall of Juiblex is proficient with all simple and martial weapons, with all types of armor, and with shields.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.70
Sickening Slime				KEY:Thrall of Juiblex ~ Sickening Slime					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Thrall of Juiblex Class Feature.SpecialQuality		DEFINE:ThrallOfJuiblexSickeningSlimeLVL|0												DESC:A thrall of Juiblex can secrete a smelly slime that coats its body in a thin layer. Anyone within 5 feet must make a Fortitude saving throw (DC 10 + the thrall's class level + Constitution bonus) or take a -1 circumstance penalty on attack rolls and skill checks, due to the outrageous odor of the slime layer.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									BONUS:VAR|SickeningSlimeDC|ThrallOfJuiblexSickeningSlimeLVL																			SOURCEPAGE:p.70	BONUS:VAR|ThrallOfJuiblexSickeningSlimeLVL|ThrallOfJuiblexLVL
Corrosive Touch				KEY:Thrall of Juiblex ~ Corrosive Touch					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Thrall of Juiblex Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:Three times per day, a thrall of Juiblex of 2nd level or higher can secrete a caustic slime on its hand that deals 2d6 points of damage. Once it is secreted, the thrall can make an attack to get the corrosive slime to damage a foe, dealing normal unarmed damage as well as the damage from the slime. Because of the corrosive slime, this attack is not considered unarmed and does not provoke attacks of opportunity.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																								BONUS:VAR|CorrosiveTouchPerDay|3	BONUS:VAR|CorrosiveTouch|2																		SOURCEPAGE:p.70
Summon Ooze					KEY:Thrall of Juiblex ~ Summon Ooze						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Thrall of Juiblex Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:At 3rd level, a thrall of Juiblex can summon a patch of green slime, a gray ooze, an ochre jelly, or a gelatinous cube as the summon monster spell with his thrall level as the caster level.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.70	BONUS:VAR|SummonOozePerDay|1
Contagion					KEY:Thrall of Juiblex ~ Contagion						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Thrall of Juiblex Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:Once per day, a thrall of Juiblex can spread a disease, as the contagion spell (caster level 10th).																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.70	BONUS:VAR|ContagionPerDay|1	BONUS:VAR|ContagionLVL|10
Alter Self					KEY:Thrall of Juiblex ~ Alter Self						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Thrall of Juiblex Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:At 4th level, a thrall of Juiblex's form becomes somewhat transitory and amorphous. It can change its appearance and form at will, as the alter self spell cast by a 4th-level caster.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.70
Summon Demon				KEY:Thrall of Juiblex ~ Summon Demon					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Thrall of Juiblex Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:A 5th-level thrall of Juiblex can summon a demon of 5 HD or less once per day. This functions as a summon monster spell cast by a 15th-level caster. A 9th-level thrall of Juiblex can summon a demon of 10 HD or less once per day.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.70	BONUS:VAR|SummonDemonPerDay|1	BONUS:VAR|SummonMajorDemonPerDay|(ThrallOfJuiblexLVL>=9)
Corrosive Spew				KEY:Thrall of Juiblex ~ Corrosive Spew					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Thrall of Juiblex Class Feature.SpecialQuality		DEFINE:ThrallOfJuiblexCorrosiveSpewLVL|0												DESC:At 6th level, a thrall of Juiblex can spit a gout of caustic goo in a line 5 feet wide and 30 feet long once per day. The corrosive spew deals 8d6 points of acid damage to anyone in its path, with a Reflex saving throw (DC 10 + thrall's class level + thrall's Con bonus) for half damage.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													BONUS:VAR|CorrosiveSpewLine|5	BONUS:VAR|CorrosiveSpewDice|8	BONUS:VAR|CorrosiveSpewDC|ThrallOfJuiblexCorrosiveSpewLVL									SOURCEPAGE:p.70	BONUS:VAR|ThrallOfJuiblexCorrosiveSpewLVL|ThrallOfJuiblexLVL
Summon Pudding				KEY:Thrall of Juiblex ~ Summon Pudding					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Thrall of Juiblex Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:At 7th level, a thrall of Juiblex can summon a black pudding as if it had cast a summon monster spell with its thrall level as the caster level.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.70	BONUS:VAR|SummonPuddingPerDay|1
Polymorph Self				KEY:Thrall of Juiblex ~ Polymorph Self					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Thrall of Juiblex Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:An 8th-level thrall of Juiblex's form is more amorphous than ever. It can change its appearance and form at will, as the polymorph self spell cast by an 8th-level caster.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.70
No Discernible Anatomy			KEY:Thrall of Juiblex ~ No Discernible Anatomy				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Thrall of Juiblex Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:At 10th level, a thrall of Juiblex's form is so amorphous that it no longer need worry about being affected by critical hits, sneak attacks, damage from poison, paralysis, or stunning. However, potions no longer affect the thrall either.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.70

# Thrall of Orcus
Weapon and Armor Proficiency		KEY:Thrall of Orcus ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Thrall of Orcus Class Feature.SpecialQuality																							DESC:A thrall of Orcus is proficient with all simple and martial weapons, with all types of armor, and with shields.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.71
Bonus Feat or Spells			KEY:Thrall of Orcus ~ Bonus Feat or Spells				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Thrall of Orcus Class Feature.SpecialQuality																							DESC:When a thrall of Orcus attains 1st, 4th, 7th, and 10th level, the character gains new spells per day as if she had also gained a level in whatever spellcasting class she belonged to before she added the prestige class, or else she gains a bonus feat of her choice. If the thrall chooses +1 spellcasting level, she does not gain any other benefit a character of that class would have gained (improved chance of controlling or rebuking undead, metamagic or item creation feats, hit points beyond those received from the prestige class, and so on), except for an increased effective level of spellcasting. This essentially means that she adds the new level to the level of whatever other spellcasting class the character has, then determines spells per day, spells known, and caster level accordingly. If a character had more than one spellcasting class before she became a thrall of Orcus, she must decide to which class she adds the level for purposes of determining spells per day. A thrall of Orcus is free to choose the bonus feat at one opportunity and the spellcasting level the next time the decision arises, or vice versa. Characters who are not spellcasters must choose the bonus feat.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.71	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Thrall of Orcus Ability|(ThrallOfOrcusLVL+2)/3
Carrion Stench				KEY:Thrall of Orcus ~ Carrion Stench					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Thrall of Orcus Class Feature.SpecialQuality			DEFINE:ThrallOfOrcusCarrionStenchLVL|0												DESC:A thrall of Orcus, when desired, emits a terrible smell in a 10-foot radius. Living creatures in the radius (excluding the thrall) must succeed at a Fortitude save (DC 10 + thrall's class level + thrall's Con modifier) or take a -2 penalty on all attack rolls, weapon damage rolls, saving throws, skill checks, and ability checks for 1 round per class level of the thrall of Orcus. Furthermore, mindless undead creatures within the radius of the stench believe the thrall of Orcus to be undead.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																										BONUS:VAR|CarrionStenchRadius|10	BONUS:VAR|CarrionStenchDC|ThrallOfOrcusCarrionStenchLVL													SOURCEPAGE:p.72	BONUS:VAR|ThrallOfOrcusCarrionStenchLVL|ThrallOfOrcusLVL
Touch of Fear				KEY:Thrall of Orcus ~ Touch of Fear						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Thrall of Orcus Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:Three times per day, a 2nd-level thrall of Orcus can produce an effect identical to that of the cause fear spell cast by a 10th-level caster.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.72	BONUS:VAR|CauseFearPerDay|3	BONUS:VAR|CauseFearLVL|10
Demon Wings					KEY:Thrall of Orcus ~ Demon Wings						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Thrall of Orcus Class Feature.SpecialQuality			DEFINE:ThrallOfOrcusDemonWingsLVL|0													DESC:Once per day, a 3rd-level thrall of Orcus can bring forth massive black wings from his back. These wings allow the thrall to fly at his normal land speed with average maneuverability. The demon wings last for up to 1 hour and are dismissible with a standard action. At 7th level, the thrall can use his demon wings at will, and they last as long as needed.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																	BONUS:VAR|DemonWingsPerDay|1	BONUS:VAR|DemonWingsPower|1	BONUS:VAR|DemonWingsPower|1|PREVARGTEQ:7,ThrallOfOrcusDemonWingsLVL							SOURCEPAGE:p.72	BONUS:VAR|ThrallOfOrcusDemonWingsLVL|ThrallOfOrcusLVL
Massive Girth/Skeletal Visage		KEY:Thrall of Orcus ~ Massive Girth/Skeletal Visage			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Thrall of Orcus Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:At 4th level, a thrall of Orcus must choose to become obese like her dread master or gaunt like an undead creature. Depending on the choice, the thrall gains the Deformity (obese) or Deformity (gaunt) feat as a bonus feat.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																				SOURCEPAGE:p.72	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Thrall of Orcus Deformity|1
Summon Undead				KEY:Thrall of Orcus ~ Summon Undead						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Thrall of Orcus Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:Once per day, a 5th-level thrall of Orcus can summon 1d4 ghouls, 1d3 shadows, 1 wight, or 1 wraith as the summon monster spell cast by a caster of her class level. At 9th level, the thrall can summon 1d3 mummies, 1 spectre, 1 mohrg, 1 vampire, or 1 ghost instead. If she chooses a vampire or a ghost, its character level is one less than the thrall's class level.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.72	BONUS:VAR|SummonUndeadPerDay|1
Pallor of Death				KEY:Thrall of Orcus ~ Pallor of Death					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Thrall of Orcus Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:A 6th-level thrall of Orcus can adopt the appearance of a humanoid undead creature of her choosing as if she had cast the alter self spell. While in this form, the thrall has an aura of fear (as the fear spell cast by a 6th-level caster) that affects only living nonoutsiders within 25 feet. Pallor of death lasts for 1 minute per class level and can be used once per day.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																											SOURCEPAGE:p.72
Death Touch					KEY:Thrall of Orcus ~ Death Touch						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Thrall of Orcus Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:An 8th-level thrall of Orcus can force a living creature hit with a touch attack to attempt a Fortitude save (DC 10 + thrall's class level + thrall's Cha bonus). If the target fails its save, it dies.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.72	BONUS:VAR|DeathTouchPerDay|1	BONUS:VAR|DeathTouchDC|ThrallOfOrcusLVL
Summon Nightwing				KEY:Thrall of Orcus ~ Summon Nightwing					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Thrall of Orcus Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:A 10th-level thrall of Orcus can summon 1 nightwing once per week, as the summon monster spell cast by a 15th-level caster.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																				SOURCEPAGE:p.72	BONUS:VAR|SummonNightwingPerWeek|1

# Ur-Priest
Weapon and Armor Proficiency		KEY:Ur-Priest ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Ur-Priest Class Feature.SpecialQuality																								DESC:An ur-priest is proficient with simple weapons, but not with armor or shields.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.72
Spells					KEY:Ur-Priest ~ Spells								CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Ur-Priest Class Feature.SpecialQuality																								DESC:An ur-priest gains the ability to cast a number of divine spells. To cast a spell, the ur-priest must have a Wisdom score of at least 10 + the spell's level, so an ur-priest with a Wisdom of 10 or lower cannot cast these spells. Urpriest bonus spells are based onWisdom, and saving throws against these spells have a DC of 10 + spell level +Wisdom modifier. When Table 5-16 indicates 0 spells of a given level, such as 0 2nd-level spells at 2nd level, the ur-priest gets only bonus spells. An ur-priest without a bonus spell for that level cannot yet cast a spell of that level. The ur-priest's spell list is identical to the cleric's spell list. An ur-priest has access to any spell on the list and prepares those spells as a cleric, except that she does not pray for spells, she just takes them. An ur-priest casts spells as a cleric ity to spontaneously cast inflict or cure spells, nor does she have domain spells or associated domain granted powers. She does not have restrictions on spells with alignments. To determine the caster level of an ur-priest, add the character's ur-priest levels to one-half of her levels in other spellcasting classes. (Any levels gained in the cleric class by an ex-cleric don't count.)																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.72
Rebuke Undead				KEY:Ur-Priest ~ Rebuke Undead							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Ur-Priest Class Feature.SpecialQuality																								DESC:Like an evil cleric, an ur-priest of 2nd level or higher can rebuke undead. She uses her ur-priest level as the cleric level for determining success and damage (see Turn and Rebuke Undead in Chapter 8 of the Player's Handbook).																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.73	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Basic Turning|Rebuke Undead	BONUS:VAR|TurnLevelBase,TurnDamagePlusBase|Ur_PriestLVL	BONUS:VAR|TurnTimesBase|3+CHA|TYPE=Base	BONUS:VAR|TurnCheckBase|CHA|TYPE=Base
Divine Spell Resistance			KEY:Ur-Priest ~ Divine Spell Resistance					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Ur-Priest Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						DESC:At 4th level, an ur-priest gains spell resistance 15, but only against divine spells and the spell-like abilities of outsiders. At 8th level, the urpriest's spell resistance increases to 20.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.73
Siphon Spell Power			KEY:Ur-Priest ~ Siphon Spell Power						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Ur-Priest Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						DESC:Because they steal whatever power they can, ur-priests learn to manipulate their energy in ways that confound other casters. A 6th-level ur-priest can temporarily sacrifice two (or more) lower-level spell slots and use those slots to prepare a higher-level spell. The hnigher-level spell must be of a level the ur-priest can cast. Only one exchange of this sort can be made each day. The levels of the lower-level slots are totaled, then reduced to three-quarters (round down) to determine the level of the extra higher-level spell slot. For example, an ur-priest who sacrifices a 3rd-level spell and a 5th-level spell can use that spell slot to prepare an additional 6th-level spell (3 + 5 = 8, and 8 ? 3/4 = 6).																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.73
Steal Spell-Like Ability		KEY:Ur-Priest ~ Steal Spell-Like Ability					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Ur-Priest Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						DESC:The most powerful urpriests can use the same techniques that siphon off the gods' spell power to steal the spell-like abilities of another creature. Once each day, when a creature with spell-like abilities is within 50 feet of a 10th-level ur-priest, the ur-priest can choose one of the spell-like abilities of the creature to steal for herself. The ur-priest can use the spell-like ability as often as the creature can, or three times per day, whichever is less.The ur-priest uses the ability as the creature does with regard to caster level and save DCs. This ability only lasts 24 hours. The creature with the spell-like ability does not lose the ability when the ur-priest steals it. If the ur-priest tries to steal a spell-like ability that the creature doesn't have, or tries to steal an ability that is supernatural rather than spell-like, the attempt automatically fails. For example, if an ur-priest is near a noble salamander, she can steal fireball and use it three times that day or steal dispel magic and use it once that day. If she is near a pit fiend, she could steal teleport without error (self plus 50 pounds of objects only) and use it three times per day, because the pit fiend can do it at will. She could even steal the pit fiend's wish ability, but because a pit fiend can only use wish once per year, the ur-priest would be similarly limited. She could not steal that power again from any creature for one year.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.73

# Vermin Lord
Weapon and Armor Proficiency		KEY:Vermin Lord ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Vermin Lord Class Feature.SpecialQuality																								DESC:A vermin lord is proficient with no weapons, armor, or shields.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.74
Spells					KEY:Vermin Lord ~ Spells							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Vermin Lord Class Feature.SpecialQuality																								DESC:When a vermin lord attains 1st level and every two levels after that (plus 10th level), the character gains new spells per day as if he had also gained a level in whatever spellcasting class he belonged to before he added the prestige class. He does not, however, gain any other benefit a character of that class would have gained (improved chance of controlling or rebuking undead, metamagic or item creation feats, hit points beyond those received from the prestige class, and so on), except for an increased effective level of spellcasting. This essentially means that he adds the new level of vermin lord to the level of whatever other spellcasting class the character has, then determines spells per day, spells known, and caster level accordingly. For example, if Silican, an 8th-level wizard, gains a level in vermin lord, he gains new spells as if he had risen to 9th level in wizard, but uses the other vermin lord aspects of level progression such as attack bonus and save bonus. If he next gains a level of wizard, making him a 9th-level wizard/1st-level vermin lord, he gains spells as if he had risen to 10th-level wizard. If a character had more than one spellcasting class before he became a vermin lord, he must decide to which class he adds the level of vermin lord.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.74
Chitin					KEY:Vermin Lord ~ Chitin							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Vermin Lord Class Feature.SpecialQuality			DEFINE:VerminlordChitinLVL|0														DESC:A vermin lord gains a +1 natural armor bonus to Armor Class from the chitinous plates that begin to grow on his flesh. Every three levels beyond 1st, this bonus increases by +1.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																															BONUS:VAR|ChitinAC|(VerminlordChitinLVL+2)/3																					SOURCEPAGE:p.74
Vermin Servant				KEY:Vermin Lord ~ Vermin Servant						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Vermin Lord Class Feature.SpecialQuality																								DESC:A vermin lord gains a servant in the form of a vermin of up to 1 HD. This servant is treated as a familiar; its intelligence increases, and it is considered a magical beast (see the Familiars section in Chapter 3 of the Player's Handbook). The vermin servant is in addition to any familiar the character may already have. A vermin lord gains additional vermin servants at higher levels. At 5th level, the vermin servant gained can be of up to 4 HD. At 9th level, the vermin servant may be of up to 16 HD.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.74	BONUS:VAR|VerminFamiliarLVL|VerminLordLVL	BONUS:VAR|VerminFamiliarLVL2|VerminLordLVL|PREVARGTEQ:VerminLordLVL,5	BONUS:VAR|VerminFamiliarLVL3|VerminLordLVL|PREVARGTEQ:VerminLordLVL,9
Blood Drain					KEY:Vermin Lord ~ Blood Drain							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Vermin Lord Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:A 2ndlevel vermin lord can grow insectoid mandibles at will. He can use these mandibles to make a bite attack that deals 1 point of damage. Furthermore, the vermin lord can attempt to start a grapple, provoking no attack of opportunity. If successful, the mandibles automatically deal 2d6 points of damage each round as they suck blood from the victim. The blood drain ability only works on living creatures.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.74
Spider Hand					KEY:Vermin Lord ~ Spider Hand							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Vermin Lord Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						DESC:Once per day, a 3rd-level vermin lord can produce an effect identical to that of a spider hand spell cast at his effective caster level.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.74	BONUS:VAR|SpiderHandPerDay|1	BONUS:VAR|SpiderHandLVL|VerminLordLVL
Swarm Armor					KEY:Vermin Lord ~ Swarm Armor							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Vermin Lord Class Feature.SpecialQuality			DEFINE:VerminlordSwarmArmorLVL|0													DESC:Each day, a 4th-level vermin lord automatically summons a swarm of insects, spiders, or scorpions that cover his flesh when he regains his spells. These insects absorb up to 10 points of damage from any damaging attack (weapons or spells). The insects die off when they absorb such attacks, and a total of up to 5 points per vermin lord level can be absorbed per day. Thus, a 7th-level vermin lord's swarm armor can absorb up to 35 points of damage, although no more than 10 points from any one attack. If a vermin lord is already wearing armor, the swarm armor has no effect.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													BONUS:VAR|SwarmArmorDamage|VerminlordSwarmArmorLVL*5																				SOURCEPAGE:p.74	BONUS:VAR|VerminlordSwarmArmorLVL|VerminLordLVL
Wings of the Vermin			KEY:Vermin Lord ~ Wings of the Vermin					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Vermin Lord Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:A vermin lord of 5th level or higher can sprout massive, buzzing insectoid wings from his back once per day. With these wings, he can fly at his normal land speed with average maneuverability for 1 hour. The vermin lord can carry his normal carrying capacity, and greater burdens affect his speed as they would affect his land speed. It is impossible to move silently with these wings.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.75	BONUS:VAR|WingsOfTheVerminPerDay|1
Spider Legs					KEY:Vermin Lord ~ Spider Legs							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Vermin Lord Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						DESC:Once per day, a 6th-level vermin lord can produce an effect identical to that of a spider legs spell cast at his effective caster level.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.75	BONUS:VAR|SpiderLegsPerDay|1	BONUS:VAR|SpiderLegsLVL|VerminLordLVL+charbonusto("CASTERLEVEL","Vermin Lord")
Spew Vermin					KEY:Vermin Lord ~ Spew Vermin							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpellLike.Class Feature.Vermin Lord Class Feature.SpecialQuality				DEFINE:VerminlordSpewVerminLVL|0	DEFINE:SpewVerminDamageDie|0								DESC:Once per day, a 7th-level vermin lord is able to spray out a swarm of vermin from his mouth, as a breath weapon in a 30-foot cone. Anyone in this area takes 1d6 points of damage per vermin lord level, with a successful Reflex save reducing the damage by half (DC 10 + vermin lord's class level + vermin lord's Con bonus). The vermin then remain as if a summon swarm spell had been cast at the vermin lord's class level. The vermin are under the command of the vermin lord.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																														BONUS:VAR|SpewVerminDamageDie|6	BONUS:VAR|SpewVerminCone|30	BONUS:VAR|SpewVerminDice|VerminlordSpewVerminLVL	BONUS:VAR|SpewVerminDC|VerminlordSpewVerminLVL	SOURCEPAGE:p.75	BONUS:VAR|VerminlordSpewVerminLVL|VerminLordLVL
Poison					KEY:Vermin Lord ~ Poison							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Class Feature.Vermin Lord Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:In a vermin lord of 8th level or higher, the mandibles gained from the blood drain ability now carry a natural venom that deals 1 point of Strength damage with each successful bite attack and 1 point of Strength damage 1 minute later. The Fortitude save DC to resist the poison is 10 + vermin lord's class level + vermin lord's Con modifier.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.75	BONUS:VAR|PoisonDC|VerminLordLVL
Hivemind					KEY:Vermin Lord ~ Hivemind							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Vermin Lord Class Feature.SpecialQuality																					DESC:A 10th-level vermin lord can form the impetus to create a hivemind (see Hivemind in Chapter 2). The hivemind must include the vermin lord, although he counts as only a single individual and his Intelligence and Charisma scores are unaffected. However, he controls the hivemind, gains the insight bonuses, and can take advantage of the spellcasting abilities of the hivemind if enough individuals are present. The vermin lord's vermin servant can also join the hivemind if the vermin lord wishes.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.75

# Warrior of Darkness
Weapon and Armor Proficiency		KEY:Warrior of Darkness ~ Weapon and Armor Proficiency		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Class Feature.Warrior of Darkness Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						DESC:A warrior of darkness is proficient with all simple and martial weapons, with all types of armor, and with shields.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.76
Black Magic Oil				KEY:Warrior of Darkness ~ Black Magic Oil					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Warrior of Darkness Class Feature.SpecialQuality		DEFINE:WarriorOfDarknessBlackMagicOilLVL|0											DESC:A warrior of darkness can use his forbidden arcane arts to create a magic oil that he anoints himself with. An individual warrior of darkness makes oil that works only on him, and he can only make one dose of the oil each time this class feature is gained (at 1st, 4th, 7th, and 10th level). When he attains an appropriate level, the warrior of darkness creates a new black magic oil and anoints himself with it. He then chooses from the above list of supernatural abilities to imbue within himself permanently, picking a choice available to him based on his class level and Charisma modifier (the highest-numbered choice possible, or any lower one). A warrior of darkness cannot choose an ability more than once.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																	DEFINE:BlackMagicOilLVL|0					BONUS:VAR|BlackMagicOilLVL|WarriorOfDarknessBlackMagicOilLVL+CHA																		SOURCEPAGE:p.76	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Black Magic Oil|((WarriorOfDarknessLVL+2)/3)					BONUS:VAR|WarriorOfDarknessBlackMagicOilLVL|WarriorOfDarknessLVL
Darkling Weapon				KEY:Warrior of Darkness ~ Darkling Weapon					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Warrior of Darkness Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:With 3 rounds of preparation (involving rituals and alchemical substances that cost 50 gp), a warrior of darkness can imbue any weapon with a +1 enhancement bonus on attack and damage rolls. If the weapon already has an enhancement bonus, the warrior of darkness can instead imbue the weapon with any magical special quality that is the equivalent of a +1 bonus (see Chapter 8 of the DUNGEON MASTER's Guide for a list of weapon qualities). The bonus or special quality only functions when the weapon is in the hands of the warrior of darkness, and it lasts 1 hour per warrior of darkness level. The warrior can imbue only one special quality in a weapon at a time.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.76
Black Magic Elixir			KEY:Warrior of Darkness ~ Black Magic Elixir				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Warrior of Darkness Class Feature.SpecialQuality		DEFINE:WarriorOfDarknessBlackMagicElixirLVL|0											DESC:At 3rd level, a warrior of darkness can use his knowledge of black magic and alchemy to create a magical elixir that he then imbibes. An individual warrior of darkness makes elixir that works only on him, and he can only make one dose of the elixir each time this class feature is gained (at 3rd, 6th, and 9th level). When he creates an elixir, the warrior of darkness chooses from the following list of supernatural abilities to imbue within himself permanently, picking a choice available to him based on his class level and Charisma modifier. No ability other than violent knowledge may be chosen more than once.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																	DEFINE:BlackMagicElixirLVL|0					BONUS:VAR|BlackMagicElixirLVL|WarriorOfDarknessBlackMagicElixirLVL+CHA																	SOURCEPAGE:p.76	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Black Magic Elixir|WarriorOfDarknessLVL/3	BONUS:VAR|WarriorOfDarknessBlackMagicElixirLVL|WarriorOfDarknessLVL
Scarred Flesh				KEY:Warrior of Darkness ~ Scarred Flesh					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Warrior of Darkness Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:Through ritual scarification, a 5thlevel warrior of darkness gains damage reduction 5/+3.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.76
Repellent Flesh				KEY:Warrior of Darkness ~ Repellent Flesh					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Class Feature.Warrior of Darkness Class Feature.SpecialQuality																				DESC:Through ritual, obscene tattooing, an 8th-level warrior of darkness gains spell resistance 20.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.76

