Spell-Like Abilities	KEY:Demon (Bar-Lgura) ~ Spell-Like Abilities				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Demon (Bar-Lgura) Race Trait.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:At will-darkness, cause fear, dispel magic, see invisibility, telekinesis; 2/day-change self, invisibility, major image. Caster level 6th; save DC 11 + spell level.
Teleport without Error	KEY:Demon (Bar-Lgura) ~ Teleport without Error				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Demon (Bar-Lgura) Race Trait.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:A bar-lgura can use this ability at will, as the spell, carrying up to 200 pounds with it. Bar-lguras can even use this ability while grappling (grapple bonus +10), but the foe must be pinned first.
Summon Tanar'ri		KEY:Demon (Bar-Lgura) ~ Summon Tanar'ri					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Demon (Bar-Lgura) Race Trait.SpecialQuality.SpellLike	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Once per day a bar-lgura can attempt to summon another bar-lgura with a 35%% chance of success.
Skills			KEY:Demon (Bar-Lgura) ~ Skills						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Demon (Bar-Lgura) Race Trait.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:The skin of a bar-lgura changes color, allowing it to blend it with surroundings like a chameleon and conferring a +4 racial bonus on Hide checks. A bar-lgura also receives a +10 racial bonus on Jump checks.

# Demon (Babau)
Sneak Attack		KEY:Demon (Babau) ~ Sneak Attack					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Demon (Babau) Race Trait.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:A babau can make a sneak attack like a rogue, inflicting +2d6 points of damage whenever a foe is denied his or her Dexterity bonus, or when the babau is flanking.
Spell-Like Abilities	KEY:Demon (Babau) ~ Spell-Like Abilities				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Demon (Babau) Race Trait.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:At will-darkness, desecrate, cause fear, dispel magic, fly, see invisibility, telekinesis, teleport without error (self plus 50 pounds of gear only); 1/day-polymorph self, wrack. Caster level 7th; save DC 13 + spell level
Weakness Gaze		KEY:Demon (Babau) ~ Weakness Gaze					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Demon (Babau) Race Trait.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:A babau has a gaze attack that deals 1d3 points of Strength damage to any creature that fails its Fortitude save (DC 16).
Protective Slime		KEY:Demon (Babau) ~ Protective Slime					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Demon (Babau) Race Trait.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Because of the slippery, slimy jelly that coats its skin, a babau takes half damage from slashing and piercing weapons. Further, any weapon that strikes it is corroded and ruined by a touch of the goo. A magic weapon must succeed at a Reflex save (DC 17) or be corroded and ruined. Bare flesh exposed to the slime (through unarmed attacks or grappling) automatically takes 1d6 points of acid damage per round or per strike.
Summon Tanar'ri		KEY:Demon (Babau) ~ Summon Tanar'ri					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Demon (Babau) Race Trait.SpecialQuality.SpellLike	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Once per day a babau can attempt to summon 1 babau with a 40%% chance of success.
Skills			KEY:Demon (Babau) ~ Skills						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Demon (Babau) Race Trait.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Babaus receive a +8 racial bonus on Hide, Listen, Move Silently, and Search checks.

# Demon (Shadow Demon)
Improved Grab		KEY:Demon (Shadow Demon) ~ Improved Grab					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Demon (Shadow Demon) Race Trait.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:If a shadow demon hits a Mediumsize or smaller opponent with both claw attacks, it deals normal damage and attempts to start a grapple as a free action without provoking an attack of opportunity (grapple bonus +17). If it hits with both claws, it can also rake in the same round. The shadow demon has the option to conduct the grapple normally, or simply use its claws to hold the opponent (-20 penalty on grapple check, but the shadow demon is not considered grappled). In either case, each successful grapple check it makes during successive rounds automatically deals damage from both claws.
Pounce			KEY:Demon (Shadow Demon) ~ Pounce						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Demon (Shadow Demon) Race Trait.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:If a shadow demon dives or leaps upon a foe during the first round of combat, it can make a full attack (including a rake attempt, see below) even though it has moved.
Rake				KEY:Demon (Shadow Demon) ~ Rake							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Demon (Shadow Demon) Race Trait.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:On any round that a shadow demon has a hold on an opponent (see Improved Grab, above), it can make two rake attacks (+17 melee touch) with its hind legs for 1d6 points of damage each. The shadow demon can also attempt to rake when it pounces on an opponent.
Spell-Like Abilities	KEY:Demon (Shadow Demon) ~ Spell-Like Abilities				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Demon (Shadow Demon) Race Trait.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:At will: darkness; 1/day-deeper darkness, damning darkness; 1/week-magic jar. Caster level 10th; save DC 15 + spell level.
Darkness Enhancement	KEY:Demon (Shadow Demon) ~ Darkness Enhancement				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Demon (Shadow Demon) Race Trait.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Shadow demons gain power from being within total darkness. They gain a +4 enhancement bonus to AC, attack rolls, damage rolls, saves, and skill and ability checks in such conditions.
Flesh-Ripping Claws	KEY:Demon (Shadow Demon) ~ Flesh-Ripping Claws				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Demon (Shadow Demon) Race Trait.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:When a shadow demon's claws touch flesh, they become corporeal, allowing the creature to claw, rake, and even grapple with opponents, yet still ignore their armor. The shadow demon's claw and rake attacks are thus made as touch attacks. Fleshless creatures, such as certain constructs, are immune to the attacks of a shadow demon. Corporeal foes attempting to grapple the shadow demon can only attempt to escape; they can't deal damage or pin in a grapple. All damage a shadow demon's claws deal is vile damage (see Vile Damage in Chapter 2).
Immunities			KEY:Demon (Shadow Demon) ~ Immunities						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Demon (Shadow Demon) Race Trait.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:A shadow demon is immune to fire, cold, and electricity as well as mind-affecting effects, poison, sleep, paralysis, stunning, and disease. It is not subject to critical hits, subdual damage, ability damage, energy drain, or death from massive damage.
Incorporeal Subtype	KEY:Demon (Shadow Demon) ~ Incorporeal Subtype				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Demon (Shadow Demon) Race Trait.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:A shadow demon can be harmed only by other incorporeal creatures, +1 or better magic weapons, spells, spell-like abilities, and supernatural abilities. The creature has a 50%% chance to ignore any damage from a corporeal source, except for force effects or attacks made with ghost touch weapons. A shadow demon can pass through solid objects, but not force effects, at will. Its attacks ignore natural armor, armor, and shields, but deflection bonuses and force effects work normally against them. A shadow demon always moves silently and cannot be heard with Listen checks if it doesn't wish to be.
Light Powerlessness	KEY:Demon (Shadow Demon) ~ Light Powerlessness				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Demon (Shadow Demon) Race Trait.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:A shadow demon is drained in bright light (such as sunlight) and flees from it. Within such light, it takes a -4 penalty to AC, attack rolls, damage rolls, saves, and skill and ability checks.
Skills			KEY:Demon (Shadow Demon) ~ Skills						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Demon (Shadow Demon) Race Trait.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:A shadow demons receives a +10 racial bonus on Hide checks.

# Demon (Chasme)
Drone				KEY:Demon (Chasme) ~ Drone							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Demon (Chasme) Race Trait.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:As a full-round action, a chasme can beat its wings to create a droning buzz in a 60-foot spread. Each creature in the area must make a Will save (DC 16) or fall asleep for 2d10 rounds. There is no Hit Dice limit for this effect. This ability otherwise functions like the sleep spell. Demons and creatures immune to sleep effects (such as elves) are immune to this effect.
Fear Aura			KEY:Demon (Chasme) ~ Fear Aura						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Demon (Chasme) Race Trait.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:As a free action, a chasme can create an aura of fear in a 5-foot radius. The effect is otherwise identical with a fear spell (caster level 10th; Will DC 16 negates). If the save is successful, that creature cannot be affected again by that chasme's fear aura for 24 hours.
Spell-Like Abilities	KEY:Demon (Chasme) ~ Spell-Like Abilities				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Demon (Chasme) Race Trait.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:At will-contagion, darkness, desecrate, detect good, dispel magic, fly, insect plague, ray of enfeeblement, protection from good, see invisibility, telekinesis, teleport without error (self plus 50 pounds of gear only), wave of grief; 1/day-circle of nausea, unholy aura. Caster level 10th; save DC 12 + spell level.
Wounding			KEY:Demon (Chasme) ~ Wounding						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Demon (Chasme) Race Trait.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:A wound resulting from a chasme's attack bleeds for an additional 1 points of damage per round thereafter. Multiple wounds from such attacks result in cumulative bleeding loss (two wounds for 2 points of damage per round, and so on). The bleeding can be stopped only by a successful Heal check (DC 10) or the application of a cure spell or some other healing spell (heal, healing circle, or the like).
Summon Tanar'ri		KEY:Demon (Chasme) ~ Summon Tanar'ri					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Demon (Chasme) Race Trait.SpecialQuality.SpellLike	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Once per day a chasme can attempt to summon 1d4 rutterkins or 1 chasme with a 40%% chance of success.

# Devil (Krochacon)
Disease			KEY:Devil (Krochacon) ~ Disease						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Devil (Krochacon) Race Trait.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Any creature hit by the kochracon's bite attack must succeed at a Fortitude save (DC 14) or contract devil chills. The incubation period is 1d4 days, and the disease deals 1d6 points of Strength damage. The victim must make three successful Fortitude saving throws in a row to recover (see Disease in Chapter 3 of the DUNGEON MASTER's Guide).
Spell-Like Abilities	KEY:Devil (Krochacon) ~ Spell-Like Abilities				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Devil (Krochacon) Race Trait.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:At will-animate dead, cure moderate wounds, desecrate, detect good, detect magic, dispel magic, magic circle against good, liquid pain, major image, sorrow, suggestion, teleport without error (self plus 50 pounds of gear only) wave of grief, wither limb, wrack; 1/day-blasphemy. Caster level 12th; save DC 13 + spell level.
Baatezu Traits		KEY:Devil (Krochacon) ~ Baatezu Traits					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Devil (Krochacon) Race Trait.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:A kocrachon can communicate telepathically with any creature within 100 feet that has a language. In addition, it can see perfectly in darkness of any kind, even that created by a deeper darkness spell. A kocrachon is immune to fire and poison, and it has acid resistance 20 and cold resistance 20.
Sadism			KEY:Devil (Krochacon) ~ Sadism						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Devil (Krochacon) Race Trait.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:For every 10 points of damage a kochrachon deals in a round, it gains a +1 luck bonus on attack rolls, saving throws, and skill checks during the next round.
Summon Baatezu		KEY:Devil (Krochacon) ~ Summon Baatezu					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Devil (Krochacon) Race Trait.SpecialQuality.SpellLike	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Twice per day a kocrachon can attempt to summon 1 kocrachon, with a 40%% chance of success.

# Devil (Ghargatula)
Improved Grab	KEY:Devil (Ghargatula) ~ Improved Grab				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Devil (Ghargatula) Race Trait.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:If a ghargatula hits a Large or smaller opponent with a bite attack, it deals normal damage and attempts to start a grapple as a free action without provoking an attack of opportunity (grapple bonus +46). If it successfully grabs a creature that it can also swallow whole (see below), it can attempt to do so in the next round. The ghargatula has the option to conduct the grapple normally, or simply use its jaws to hold the opponent (-20 penalty on grapple check, but the ghargatula is not considered grappled). In either case, each successful grapple check it makes during successive rounds automatically deals bite damage.
Swallow Whole	KEY:Devil (Ghargatula) ~ Swallow Whole				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Devil (Ghargatula) Race Trait.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:A ghargatula can try to swallow a Medium-size or smaller opponent that is already in its mouth by making a successful grapple check (grapple bonus +46). The swallowed creature takes 2d8+8 points of crushing damage per round and 8 points of acid damage from the ghargatula's innards. A swallowed creature can cut its way out by using claws or a Small or Tiny slashing weapon to deal 25 points of damage to the innards (AC 20). Once the creature exits, muscular action closes the hole; another swallowed opponent must again cut its own way out. The ghargatula's innards can hold 2 Medium-size, 8 Small, 32 Tiny, or 128 Diminutive or smaller opponents.
Poison		KEY:Devil (Ghargatula) ~ Poison					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Devil (Ghargatula) Race Trait.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Each successful tail stinger attack delivers a gharagatula's poison (Fort DC 34). The initial and secondary damage is the same (2d6 points of Dexterity damage).
Baatezu Traits	KEY:Devil (Ghargatula) ~ Baatezu Traits				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Devil (Ghargatula) Race Trait.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:A ghargatula can communicate telepathically with any creature within 100 feet that has a language. In addition, it can see perfectly in darkness of any kind, even that created by a deeper darkness spell. A ghargatula is immune to fire and poison, and it has acid resistance 20 and cold resistance 20.

# Eye Of Fear And Flame
Eye of Fear			KEY:Eye Of Fear And Flame ~ Eye of Fear						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Eye Of Fear And Flame Race Trait.SpecialQuality.SpellLike	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Once per round, as a free action, an eye of fear and flame can produce an effect identical with that of a fear spell out of its black gem-eye. Caster level 15th; Will DC 17 negates.
Eye of Flame		KEY:Eye Of Fear And Flame ~ Eye of Flame					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Eye Of Fear And Flame Race Trait.SpecialQuality.SpellLike	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:Once every three rounds, as a standard action, an eye of fear and flame can produce a fireball from its red gemeye. Caster level 15th; Reflex DC 13 half. The fireball deals 10d6 points of fire damage, plus half again as much damage if empowered. If the fireball is corrupted, one-half of the damage is unholy damage that affects even those immune to fire.
Spell-Like Abilities	KEY:Eye Of Fear And Flame ~ Spell-Like Abilities				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Eye Of Fear And Flame Race Trait.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:At will-detect good, detect law, detect thoughts, true seeing (divine spell); 2/day-ethereal jaunt. Caster level 15th; save DC 14 + spell level.
Immunities			KEY:Eye Of Fear And Flame ~ Immunities						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Eye Of Fear And Flame Race Trait.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:An eye of fear and flame is immune to cold. Because it lacks flesh or internal organs, it takes only half damage from piercing and slashing weapons.
Spell Deflection		KEY:Eye Of Fear And Flame ~ Spell Deflection					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Eye Of Fear And Flame Race Trait.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:If any sort of vision-affecting spell such as blindness or power word, blind is cast on an eye of fear and flame, it is reflected back upon the caster (as the spell turning spell), who must save against the effect of her own spell.
Turn Resistance		KEY:Eye Of Fear And Flame ~ Turn Resistance					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Eye Of Fear And Flame Race Trait.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:An eye of fear and flame is treated as an undead with 16 Hit Dice for the purpose of turn, rebuke, command, and bolster attempts.
Undead Traits		KEY:Eye Of Fear And Flame ~ Undead Traits					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Eye Of Fear And Flame Race Trait.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:An eye of fear and flame is immune to mind-affecting effects, poison, sleep, paralysis, stunning, disease, death effects, necromantic effects, and any effect that requires a Fortitude save unless it also works on objects. It is not subject to critical hits, subdual damage, ability damage, ability drain, energy drain, or death from massive damage. An eye of fear and flame cannot be raised, and resurrection works only if it is willing. The creature has darkvision (60-foot range).

